One hundred twenty-six flowers and 94 buds on 15 mature inflorescences and two immature upright inflorescences; plant 43cm wide, grown in a 15-cm pot; sepals and petals white, irregular deep rose markings proximally; lip yellow, rose markings; substance moderately firm; texture crystalline.

Five large, stunning flowers arranged evenly on one 12.5-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals slightly undulate, olive green heavily overlaid cordovan, spotted darker cordovan distal two-thirds, undulate margins; lip cream-white, trilobed, heavily veined dark magenta, mid-lobe broad, fan-shaped, slightly ruffled, throat bright yellow, side lobes closed over column; column white blotched dark magenta; substance firm; texture satiny; commended for size and floriferousness.

crossvalue: (Rhyncholaeliocattleya Waikiki Gold x Rhyncholaeliocattleya Vicky Nazareno)
description: Six extremely fragrant flowers and one bud on one 13-cm semi-pendant inflorescence; sepals and petals light yellow-green, petals faint pink venation; lip ruffled, white, symetrical dark pink areas each side, darker pink veins, seperated by light yellow central region, throat overlaid bright yellow; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Masdevallia Pixie Snow Leopard x Masdevallia John Leathers)
description: One attractive flower and one bud on two 36-cm inflorescences;    dorsal sepal white, caudae 4.5cm, orange tip; lateral sepals white blushed raspberry pink veined darker, dark pink-red linear markings proximally, straight caudae 3.5cm, orange tips; petals minute, white; lip minute, white tipped gold; column and anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte; caudae length included in sepal length measurement.

Two dangling flowers and three buds on two inflorescences up to 62cm; dorsal sepal completely recurved into a tube, barely visible white background overlaid rose except basally; synsepal white marked marginally rose, more pronounced at the midrib and margin; petals twisted one quarter turn, white mostly overlaid rose, lighter at the lower margin; pouch full, white blushed rose frontally, spotted purple, sparse rose blothching internally; staminode hirsute, white overlaid rose, more strongly at margin; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Zygopetalum B. G. White x Zygopetalum James Strauss)
description: Five flowers on one inflorescence; sepals and petals chartreuse heavily blotched dark mahogany; lip white, overlaid purple waterfall;  substance very firm; texture matte.

One shapely flower on one inflorescence; sepals cream, shading to green at distal third; petals cream, shading to green distally; lip white, sidelobes yellow; column and anther cap white; substance heavy; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Phar Lap x Cymbidium Rio Rita)
description: Forty-three flowers and six buds on a single arching pendant inflorescence; sepals and petals maroon with darker midline and cream edge; lip saturated ruby, keel cream; pollen cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Five flowers on one 12-cm upright inflorescence; sepals lanceolate, white marked green at the tip; petals white overlaid light purple on the edge and dark purple on the distal half; lip strongly frilled at the central margin, side lobes partially closed over the column, white, strongly marked purple at the margins; column white mostly overlaid purple, anther cap white, substance firm; texture matte.

One hundred sixty flowers and 18 buds on 22 upright 38-cm inflorescences; 50 x 60-cm plant growing in a 23-cm plastic pot; sepals white blushed pale pink; petals white; lip white, throat dark maroon striations, yellow central callus,  pink distally; substance firm; texture satin.  Reference award #20174106.

Twelve flowers on one 25-cm upright, branched inflorescence;  sepals spatulate, reflexed, dark purple; petals threadlike, chartreuse, purple distally; lip sharply recurved, dark purple, white callus centrally; column white, anther cap white; substance firm; texture waxy.

Eight flowers on one 20-cm inflorescence; sepals white, sparsely spotted fuchsia; petals white, fuchsia flush apically; lip white, broad margin deep fuchsia transitioning to striations in throat; column white, light fuchsia blush, anther cap white; substance firm; texture waxy.

crossvalue: (Phragmipedium dalessandroi x Phragmipedium QF Naukana Kealoha)
description: Three flowers on one branched inflorescence; dorsal sepal flat, yellow lightly overlaid orange; synsepal yellow overlaid light orange; petals undulating, light red-orange, yellow basally; pouch yellow, overlaid red-orange, margin yellow spotted red-orange; substance moderate; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Phalaenopsis Mount Lip x Phalaenopsis Yu Pin Easter Island)
description: Eleven well-proportioned Broad Lip flowers and three buds on one 110cm arching inflorescence; sepals and petals pale lavender-pink, petals blushed darker lavender centrally; lip side lobes broadened and partly fused with base of midlobe, all deep lavender, calli pale yellow and white; column white with fuchsia spots, anther cap white; substance fair; texture matte.

Forty-one slightly cupped flowers and 45 buds on 19 erect 17-cm average inflorescences; sepals and petals white overlaid vibrant fuchsia distal three-fourths; lip white overlaid light fuchsia, darker centrally; column bright fuchsia, anther cap white; substance firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium goeringii 'Black Lotus' x Cymbidium Voodoo 'Gypsy Red')
description: Six flat flowers on two 18.5-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals maroon, margins light green; lip white, yellow throat, keels bright yellow, side lobes spotted maroon, midlobe slightly curvedunder, blotched dark maroon distally; substance average; texture matte.

location: Peninsula Orchid Society and Gold Coast Cymbidium Society Show
description: Thirty-two flowers and 69 buds on 14 up to 4.2-cm inflorescences; borne on a scandent, rhizomatous, leafless plant; inflorescences arising from the junction between rhizome and roots; dorsal sepal erect, widely elliptic, acute, yellow-brown; lateral sepals slightly reflexed, widely elliptic, acute, yellow-brown; petals minute, triangular, light green-brown; lip white, midlobe obcordate, spur 0.5 cm in length, yellow-brown; column erect, orange, anther cap orange; substance thin; texture matte; awarded as an unusal species for North American culture; general appearance mostly roots; an interesting example of a leafless orchid.

One hundred three flowers and 19 buds on 12 up-to 17-cm inflorescences; flowers light yellow; sepals and petals spotted brick red basally, random sepals and petals streaked brick red; lip saccate, overlaid orange on mentum, gold spot on apex, lateral lobes overlaid orange; substance firm; texture crystalline.
Twenty-two flowers on two erect 29-cm inflorescences; sepals white densely spotted magenta, caudae orange; petals white;  lip yellow; substance firm; texture matte.

One flower on one 28-cm inflorescence; flower chartreuse; dorsal sepal curved forward, overlaid light brown, random cream spots; lateral sepals porrect, gently twisted distally, overlaid light brown; petals minute, not measurable; lip chartreuse overlaid light brown; substance firm; texture matte.

Approximately two thousand one hundred flowers on 2100 inflorescences; grown on a 50-cm x 50-cm plastic propagation flat; sepals and petals old gold overlaid brown; lip cream; column tan; substance soft; texture matte; lack of grooming on upper portion of plant precluded a higher score.

crossvalue: (Cattleya Seagulls Apricot x Cattleya Circle of Life)
description: Two flowers on one 11-cm inflorescence; sepals apricot veined red; petals apricot veined red, splashed darker red fanning midline to apex;  lip bright yellow, midlobe fully flushed intense crimson; column pale pink, anther cap white; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Three slightly cupped non-resupinate flowers on three 0.8-cm inflorescences; dorsal sepal white overlaid fuchsia basal two-thirds; lateral sepals white heavily overlaid fuchsia except outer edge; petals white overlaid fuchsia basal one-third; lip white suffused fuchsia meeting burnt orange at edge, dark brown margin; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Fifty-five flowers and one bud on six up to 31-cm upright inflorescences; sepals tips slightly recurved, lavender; petals slightly ruffled, tips recurved, lavender, darker distally; lip tubular, margin ruffled, intense purple, lighter centrally; column cream; substance firm; texture crystalline;  received CCE 90 award# 20225350.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Bayaka Pendant x Cymbidium Mighty Tracey)
description: Twenty-seven nicely flat flowers and one bud on two inflorescences; sepals and petals clear chartreuse; lip cream, burgundy markings; column cream overlaid pale burgundy dots; anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Lambert Day x Cymbidium Karen Hawaiian)
description: Fifty-three slightly cupped flowers and three buds on three up to 88-cm pendent inflorescences; sepals and petals yellow overlaid and speckled dark rose coalescing into stripes, yellow picotee; lip yellow overlaid maroon spots; column yellow brushed dark rose apically, maroon spots basally and underside, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Ten flowers and one bud on a graceful 19-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals bright yellow, spotted dark chocolate; lip bright yellow, spotted deep mahogany, callus bright yellow, spotted randomly orange; column white, anther cap light green; substance hard; texture crystalline.

Ten flowers on two 41-cm inflorescences; sepals green overlaid bronze; petals green overlaid bronze, intense burgundy marking proximal three-fourths, widest at base, narrowing along petal; lip white, short burgundy stripe center vein distally, additional burgundy marks each side of stripe; column green, anther cap white; substance medium-firm; texture matte.

location: Santa Clara Valley Orchid Society Show
description: Eight very flat flowers on eight inflorescences; sepals and petals vermillion; lip yellow overlaid maroon stripes basally, vermillion distally; substance medium; texture crystalline.

Four hundred fifty-seven flowers and 45 buds on 30 up to 22-cm arched inflorescences; 47-cm by 29-cm plant gracefully blooming on a 7.5-cm by 21-cm wooden mount; flowers golden yellow; sepals slender; petals ovate, slightly rolled on upper margins; lip semi-saccate; substance hard; texture waxy; the plant was immaculate and the overall appearance was improved by the more compact blooming compared with the previous award #20245351.

One flat flower on one inflorescence; sepals yellow-green tipped burgundy; horizontal petals bright chartreuse tesselated burgundy; pouch chartreuse, speckled burgundy interior, visible exterior; staminode cream overlaid dark burgundy;  substance firm; texture velvet.

Twenty-five flowers and three buds on ten inflorescences; sepals light green, heavily striated burgundy; petals light green, lightly striated burgundy, heavily marked at base; lip cream, lightly marked scarlet, mid lobe recurved; pollen cap cream; substance firm; texture matte; also awarded a CCM of 85 points, award 20194859; awarded as Cymbidium tortisepalum; SITF has determined, with the help of Ken Jacobsen that this is the natural hybrid x nishiuchianum (goeringii x kanran), based on the leaf articulation and the sub equal or shorter inflorescences (May 2019).

Seven well-arranged flowers on two up to 24-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals light yellow, suffused rose, veins iridescent rose; petals ruffled edges, suffused darker rose proximally; lip ruffled edges, white, heavily overlaid dark magenta distally, tip lighter magenta, white picotee, throat striated dark magenta; substance firm; texture crystalline.
Fifty-two flowers and seven buds on two inflorescences and 19 buds on one immature inflorescence; sepals and petals chartreuse; lip yellow, throat burgundy; substance firm; texture matte.

Forty-three flowers and 55 buds on eight up to 24-cm upright or slightly arching inflorescences; sepals and petals white, blotched and spotted pink, barred dark red basally, spotted red centrally on reverse; lip white, blotched yellow, saccate; substance firm; texture crystalline.
Two hundred twenty-six flowers and 22 buds on 25 clustered inflorescences; cascading down a 19-cm long by 9-cm wide cork mount; flowers white, overlaid blue-green;  substance firm; texture matte.

Three well-arranged flowers on one 19-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals light yellow, suffused rose, iridescent rose veins; petals ruffled edges, darker rose proximally; lip ruffled edges, white, veined dark magenta throughout, distal half heavily overlaid dark magenta, tip lighter magenta, white picotee; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Four flat flowers well displayed on one 32-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals posterior light rose, anterior white; lip white, dark rose distal half, white margin; column fused, pale green, hirsute, hairs purple, three striking mahogany spots distally; substance medium; texture crystalline.

One striking upright, oblong flower on one 41-cm inflorescence; sepals orange overlaid vermillion, darker vermillion striations, caudae dark vermillion, lateral caudae symetrically crossed; petals minute, white; lip minute, white overlaid intense purple; column and anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Phaleanopsis An Tai Spot x Phalaenopsis Brother Purple)
description: Ten beautifully spaced flowers on two arching inflorescences, one 40 cm and one 50 cm long; sepals and petals very pale green entirely overlaid with coalesced fine deep-magenta spots; lip dark magenta, interior side lobes golden; column white; substance very heavy; texture lacquered.

Sixty-eight flowers and two buds on 13 inflorescences on a 32-cm x 60-cm mounted plant with 22 branched growths, 13 bearing flowers; sepals and petals white; lip white striped purple; substance papery; texture matte.

location: Santa Clara Valley Orchid Society Meeting
description: Twelve flowers classically displayed on one upright to arching inflorescence; sepals and petals cream overlaid with medium pink striations;

Twelve well-arranged fully flat flowers and 13 buds on one 95-cm branched inflorescence; sepals and petals white blushed pink proximally;  lip white, midlobe blushed yellow tiny red spots proximally, side-lobes yellow blush distal edges, red spotting proximally, callus pale yellow, red markings; substance medium; texture slightly crystalline.

Thirty bright flowers and 40 buds on five arched inflorescences up to 20cm; sepals and petals ovate, white overlaid dark pink basally, suffused pink distally; lip white spotted yellow and orange, interior dark pink; column yellow; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Nine flowers and three buds on one infloresence; dorsal sepal light green, edge orange; lateral sepals cream, edges orange; petals cream, tip orange; lip orange-red, 4.8-cm nectary orange;  substance moderate; texture matte.

Seven flowers on one 21-cm inflorescence; sepals white, dusted fuchsia spots; petals white, distal half overlaid fuchsia; lip white, side lobes overlaid dark fuchsia margins, midlobe fully overlaid dark fuchsia transitioning to striations in throat; column white blushed lavender, anther cap white; substance firm; texture waxy.

Three flowers on two inflorescences; dorsal sepal pale green overlaid rose, striped maroon; synsepal pale green, lightly striped maroon; petals pale green overlaid burgundy, strongly tesselated dark burgundy; pouch cream, blushed rose; staminoid yellow, spotted maroon; substance average; texture waxy.

Seven flat flowers and five buds on one branched 51.5-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals bright yellow-orange, striped dark burnt orange; lip bright orange, red veins in throat, darker orange at margin, nectary 3.5cm green overlaid orange; column green, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

One striking flower on one 19.5-cm inflorescence; sepals white overlaid light green centrally, boldly striped dark green; petals hirsute, light golden yellow striped dark green, spotted dark mahogany along top edge and randomly at mid-vein and below basally, suffused rose distally; pouch green suffused dark rose, dark green venation; staminode green overlaid dark rose; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Rhyncattleanthe Elain Taylor x Cattleya Circle of Life)
description: Two round flat flowers on one 6.0-cm inflorescence; sepals orange-red, lateral sepals yellow-orange centrally, magenta veins; petals slightly reflexed at tip, orange-red, magenta veins; lip ruffled, bright gold centrally, scarlet distally and along edge; column and anther cap white; substance firm; texture velvet.

Four flowers and two buds on one infloresence; dorsal sepal orange-pink shading to olive at base; lateral sepals light orange-pink; petals light coral-pink; lip stronger orange-pink, 5.2-cm nectary pink basally, pink-brown distally;  substance good; texture matte.

Nine flat flowers and two buds on 11 28-cm upright staked inflorescences; sepals ivory: petals ivory, spotted rasberry red basally; lip ivory, heavily overlaid yellow adaxial surface, burgundy basally, callus yellow; column ivory, heavily overlaid yellow, burgundy basally, anther cap ivory; substance firm; texture satin.

Twenty-one flowers no buds nicely held on two arching inflorescences; 14 cm plant mounted on 16 cm branch wood; flowers uniformly white, nectaries 8 cm long, white at base transitioning to pink-brown at apex; lip pale chartreuse, darker centrally, keel edged burgundy; substance firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Phalaenopsis Tiannong Lucky x Phalaenopsis I-Hsin Song)
description: Twelve richly hued flowers and 3 buds on one arching 94cm inflorescence; sepals and petals white overlaid almost fully with heavy fuchsia except for a very narrow, but distinct, white picotee, lateral sepals dark purple-dotted basally; lip dark fuchsia with white picotee on the side lobes, calli lemon yellow spotted with fuchsia; column fuchsia, anther cap white; substance average; texture crystalline.

Approximately 24,000 flowers and buds on approximately 600 gently arched inflorescences in various stages of maturity; evenly distributed circumferentially over a 59-cm x 87-cm plant, grown on a 30-cm x 16-cm tree fern block;   flowers straw;   substance firm; texture satin.

crossvalue: (Phal Dragon Tree Eagle x Phal Joshua Irwin Ginsberg)
description: Three flat, well-proportioned flowers on two inflorescences; dorsal sepal green-yellow, heavily overlaid fuschia centrally, heavily overlaid magenta distally; lateral sepals green-yellow, superior halves overlaid magenta basally, inferior halves heavily overlaid magenta; petals green-yellow, concentrically barred magenta basally; lip white, overlaid fuschia, side lobes yellow; column fuchsia, anther cap fuchsia; substance hard; texture waxy. substance hard; texture waxy.

Fifty-nine well arranged flowers on five arching, 75-cm average, inflorescences well presented above gracefully arching leaves; 63-cm x 104-cm plant grown in 17-cm one-gallon plastic pot in a mixture of coconut chips, perlite, bark; dorsal sepal hooded, sepals and petals pale yellow-green overlaid dusty rose, irregular cordovan spots and stripes; lip side lobes light yellow, irregular cordovan markings, midlobe white, irregular burgundy-red markings, keel light yellow, sparsely spotted burgundy red; column cream, inferior surface randomly spotted maroon, superior surface overlaid rose, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte;  also awarded an AM, #20225409.
Three flowers on one inflorescence; sepals and petals vibrant pink, darker at base; lip pink, fringed dark red-purple ; substance moderately heavy; texture matte.

Five fairly flat flowers and one bud on six upright 14-cm inflorescences; sepals pubescent basally, recurved apically, chartreuse, stippled light burgundy distal half; petals porrect, overlapping, recurved apically, white; lip cymbiform, recurved apically, bright yellow spotted burgundy, callus yellow; substance firm; texture silky-matte.

Approximately one thousand four hundred fifty tiny flowers and approximately 1200 buds on 18 14-cm branched inflorescences; 8 immature inflorescences; 47x22-cm plant, foliage in excellent condition, grown on 9x14-cm cork slab; dorsal sepal violet; lateral sepals white, overlaid violet proximally; petals violet; lip white, spur violet;  substance not described; texture matte.

location: National Cheng Kung University Fall Orchid Show, Taiwan
description: One full flower on one 9-cm erect inflorescence; sepals creamy pale green flushed raspberry basally; petals cream, boldly tessellated rich raspberry, intense burgundy overlaid white hirsute basally; pouch cream, flushed light pink; staminode cream, raspberry markings; substance firm; texture matte.

One flower and one bud on one staked inflorescence; sepals white, well defined mahogany stripes; petals white overlaid deep mahogany, striped mahogany proximally, hirsuite edges;  pouch yellow overlaid chestnut, darker veins;  staminode chestnut, hirsuite margins; substance firm; texture matte.

Eight flowers and five buds on one upright 18-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals crystalline white, barred orange-red centrally; saccate lip orange, side lobes barred red, orange at tip ; substance medium; texture cryatalline.
One flower and one bud on one 32-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal orange; synsepal yellow-orange; petals red-orange; pouch red-orange, yellow internally; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Vanda Ben Berliner x Vandachostylis Pine Rivers)
description: Thirty-four flowers and nine visible buds with immature buds on three inflorescences; sepals and petals dark purple with lighter veins centrally; lip purple-black; substance firm; texture matte.

Twenty-eight flowers and two buds on 30 inflorescences; 44-cm diameter plant grown in 15-cm plastic pot; sepals concave, green-yellow, striped maroon; petals porrect, bright yellow, striped maroon ; lip bright yellow, speckled maroon; anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Approximately 240 flowers and six buds on 24 7.9-cm inflorescences; arising from leaf axils on four fanlike growths on a 7-cm x 5-cm cork mount, leaves 0.6cm wide, 5.5cm long, fine white roots with white hairs, root tips green; flowers translucent white; sepals and petals lanceolate; spadelike lip translucent white; anther cap bright green; pollinia yellow; substance translucent; texture crystalline; light, grass like fragrance.

Six flowers and one bud on one 70-cm arching inflorescence; dorsal sepal arching forward, yellow heavily overlaid dark red, veins and margins very dark; lateral sepals slightly reflexed, yellow heavily overlaid dark red except centrally on each side of very dark central vein; petals reflexed, some curling at side margins, yellow overlaid dark red, darker mid-rib, distal edges yellow; lip white, purple markings, callus white, purple markings, side-lobes yellow, purple markings; column arched, yellow, purple spotting; substance firm; texture matte. AD is awarded for maintaining the erythraeum species charm while introducing intense color from a standard cymbidium.

Hybridizer Santa Barbara Orchid Estate.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Lambert Day x Cymbidium Karen Hawaiian)
description: Forty-six flat round flowers on two up to 96-cm arched inflorescences; sepals and petals elliptical, burnt umber, dark veins, more prominent midline; lip orange-yellow overlaid maroon along edge, black-maroon blotches and spots, dark maroon line centrally; column orange-yellow spotted maroon, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte; upgrade from previous award 20225258.

One flower and two buds on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal light yellow overlaid centrally light green with a distinct brown stripe on midvein; synsepal light green;  petals yellow with fine brown speckles and a thin brown stripe on midline; pouch yellow fading to pale yellow distally; staminode yellow; substance firm; texture glossy.

Two flat flowers on two 13-cm inflorescences; dorsal sepal ovate, chartreuse overlaid rose, veined darker rose, pale green basally; lateral sepals rhomboid, chartreuse densley speckled rose, all three caudae chartreuse, 4.4 cm long; petals minute, white; lip minute, rose; column purple, anther cap dark purple; substance average; texture matte.

Ten flowers and two buds on one 38-cm pendent inflorescence, ten buds on an immature inflorescence; sepals and petals lanceolate, creamy white, pale salmon basally, sepals recurved, tipped pale salmon, petals retrorse; lip creamy white, salmon basally, nectary 15.2 cm, pale salmon ; substance firm; texture diamond dust.

One flower on one sturdy 15cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal white, light green centrally, veined darker green, 2.4-cm white margin; synsepal light green; petals light yellow-green; pouch light yellow-green; staminode light yellow-green; substance firm; texture matte.
Three flowers on one inflorescence; sepals and petals red-bronze; lip white veined dark purple in throat coalescing to dark purple centrally, lighter purple distally; substance firm; texture matte

Twenty flowers and nine buds on two up to 68.4-cm upright inflorescences;  sepals and petals olive green overlaid bold burgundy bars, coalescing apically; lip light ochre finely veined rose, callus bright purple; column yellow overlaid burgundy blotches apical half, anther cap white; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Six flowers and one bud on seven 17-cm inflorescences; flowers magenta, gold caudae, dorsal cauda 4.8cm, lateral caudae 3.0cm, dorsal sepal lighter magneta, lateral sepals intense magenta, dark purple veins; petals minute, purple; lip purple; column white; substance very firm; texture velvet.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Dream Therapy x Cymbidium Colonial Dawn)
description: Twenty-one flowers on two inflorescences; sepals and petals clear butter yellow; lip yellow with darker yellow markings distally; column cream, spotted red-brown;  substance firm; texture matte.

Fifteen flowers and three buds on eighteen inflorescences; leaves oblong 2.2 cm x 30 cm; sepals cream, surface hairs cream, dark burgundy spots diffused on ventral surface, caudae dark burgundy; petals dark burgundy; lip light pink; substance firm; texture hairy.

crossvalue: (Papiopedilum Donna Hanes x Paphiopedilum Billy Bunter)
description: One flower on one 11.2-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal pinched centrally, chartreuse-yellow, radially veined tan from base to 2.9 cm, white margin; synsepal  green, edge white; petals yellow upper (superior) half, chartreuse lower (inferior) half; pouch yellow overlaid tan; staminode minute, yellow; substance heavy; texture waxy; upgraded from previous HCC award to AM due to better form and larger size.

Fifteen flowers on twelve inflorescences; 12-cm diameter asian pot, plant 45cm wide, 33cm high; sepals light green, striped dark green; petals white, striped mahogany; lip white, spotted mahogany, side lobes solid dark mahogany; substance firm; texture waxy.

Twenty-three flowers and 14 buds on five arching to pendulous inflorescences up to 70cm; dorsal sepal hooded, lanceolate, light yellow spotted and blushed burgundy; lateral sepals lanceolate, light yellow, densely spotted burgundy; petals lanceolate, light yellow spotted burgundy, coalescing to blotches centrally; lip light yellow, blotched burgundy; column pale yellow blushed burgundy distally, anther cap cream;  substance average; texture matte.

One hundred thirty flowers and 116 buds on 31 inflorescences; sepals and petals white, irregularly overlaid pink distally and densely spotted dark rose basally; lip yellow; substance firm; texture matte.

Twenty-four flowers well-arranged spirally around one 22-cm inflorescence;  seven dark green leaves, midridge white up to 4.0cm wide, 7.5cm long; stem cordovan 14cm; sepals green overlaid rose; petals minute, green; tubular portion lip saccate, cordovan; distal portion lip bilobed, white; substance firm; texture matte; commended for shape and arrangement of flowers.

Eight flowers on one  42-cm inflorescence, one immature inflorescence;  sepals yellow overlaid brown-mahogany bands; petals slightly ruffled, recurved at apex, yellow overlaid mahogany basal half; lip flared, white, large burgundy spots basally; substance firm; texture lacquer.

Forty-seven pristine flowers and nine buds on 30 up to 12-cm inflorescences; immaculate well grown 27-cm x 25-cm plant mounted on 9-cm x 15-cm cork slab; dorsal sepal white, cauda light gold, pronounced raised mid-rib; lateral sepals and caudae light gold; petals and caudae light gold fading to light green centrally; lip white, nectary 9.3-cm, pale green, pale gold distally; substance firm; texture satin; also received award 20235367.

crossvalue: (Phalaenopsis Dotty Woodson x Phalaenopsis Penang Girl)
description: Four flowers and four buds on two inflorescences; sepals green, completely overlaid orange-red, green mid-line keel on dorsal surface of sepals; petals red-orange; lip white, side lobes overlaid yellow, midlobe magenta; substance firm; texture glossy.

Seventy-eight flowers on 13 pendent inflorescences; leaves lanceolate, 4.5 to 6.1 cm long x 1.5 to 1.7 cm wide; sepals burnt orange overlaid mahogany; petals mahogany; lip dark mahogany; column white; substance firm; texture matte.

Eleven full round flowers and two buds on one inflorescence; sepals ivory lightly suffused pale blush, mahogany proximally; petals ivory, mahogany proximally; lip pale yellow, mahogany spotting, side lobes darker mahogany spotting; column light yellow; substance firm; texture crystalline.

One flower and one bud on one 29.5-cm sequentially blooming inflorescence; dorsal sepal white overlaid light green medially, heavily spotted burgundy, speckled marginally; synsepal white overlaid light green, light burgundy veins, burgundy spots proximal 2/3; petals light green overlaid burgundy except spotted burgundy proximally; pouch 30-degree angle from vertical, light green overlaid burgundy; staminode light green overlaid burgundy; substance medium; texture glossy.

Seventy-eight striking, slightly cupped flowers and one bud on five up to 21.5-cm inflorescences; sepals cream overlaid deep burgundy apical two-thirds, lateral sepal falcate; petals cream blotched burgundy basally, apical two-thirds deep burgundy; lip trilobed, cream, sidelobes heavily overlaid and striped burgundy, midlobe blotched dark burgundy, callis light yellow; column cream; substance medium; texture glossy.

Five non-resupinate flowers on five 4.0-cm inflorescences; flowers pale chartreuse; sepals ovate; petals spatulate; lip cymbiform, orange spots on distal margin, spur 1.4 cm; column and anther cap cream; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Sixteen flowers on one mature inflorescence, two immature inforescences; sepals cordovan, slightly revolute; petals green overlaid cordovan stripes; lip dark cordovan, asymetrically reflexed; substance firm; texture waxy.

crossvalue: (Cattleya Circle of Life x Rhyncattleanthe Love Sound)
description: Eight full flowers and one bud on three inflorescences; sepals and petals yellow, overlaid and flared rose; lip ruffled, dark yellow, margins and distal third dark magneta, basally veined dark rose; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Two hundred thirty-five flowers and six buds on four double-branched inflorescences plus what are apparently older un-branched inflorescenses with fewer flowers and some buds, on 96 cm high plant (including inflorescences) grown in 20 cm pot; sepals and petals yellow-green almost completely overlaid red-purple, leaving base color exposed as narrow picotee edge and variously as small spots; lip white, three-lobed with lighter red-purple markings; substance firm; texture matte.

Forty-seven pristine flowers and nine buds on 30 up to 12-cm inflorescences; immaculate well grown 27-cm x 25-cm plant mounted on 9-cm x 15-cm cork slab; dorsal sepal white, cauda light gold, pronounced raised mid-rib; lateral sepals and caudae light gold; petals and caudae light gold fading to light green centrally; lip white, nectary 9.3-cm, pale green, pale gold distally; substance firm; texture satin; also received award 20235368.

Two flowers on two 4.6-cm inflorescences; dorsal sepal strongly yellow speckled purple, concentrated at midrib, cauda yellow-green, 5.9cm of the 7.4-cm dorsal length; lateral sepals white, caudae yellow-green, 5.0cm of the 7.2-cm lateral length ; petals minute, white; lip white, edged purple, purple spots; substance light-medium; texture matte.

Five striking flowers and three buds on eight inflorescences; sepals saturated cerise, clear lemon-yellow basally; petals white; lip clear lemon yellow, darker distally; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cattleya Tropical Sunset x Rhyncattleanthe Laughing Boy)
description: Three well presented flowers on one inflorescence; sepals light pink, darker pink midline; petals solid magenta, darker midline; lip white overlaid dark magenta apically; column white blotched magenta distally; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Two flowers on one inflorescence; sepals dark rose; petals dark rose, ruffled and notched upper margin; lip dark magenta apically, throat yellow, rose venation; column white flushed rose; substance good; texture crystalline.

One hundred seventy-six flowers on eight inflorescences; dorsal sepal and petals cream; lateral sepals cream spotted purple basally;   lip cream, side lobes spotted purple; substance firm; texture waxy.

Approximately two thousand eight hundred seventy-five flowers and 345 buds on 23 arching inflorescences up to 50cm distributed completely around plant; plant pristine, diameter 150cm, height above pot 90cm, circumference 500cm, grown in bark in a 40-cm diameter plastic pot; sepals and petals semi-porrect, ivory; lip ivory spotted dark purple, keels yellow; anther cap ivory; substance average; texture matte.

One large flower on one 14-cm staked inflorescence; dorsal sepal recurved, downy, white, veined purple, distal strong reticulations purple; synsepal white, veined purple; petals down-swept, recurved, white, veined purple, overlaid green proximally, superior margins edged purple, hirsute, margins undulate; pouch pale chartreuse, veined light mahogany, darker mahogany vein centrally, heavily speckled purple internally; staminode chartreuse, stippled purple, superior half reticulated green; substance firm; texture velvet, pouch glossy.

One large well presented flower and one bud on two inflorescences; sepals white, overlaid rose; petals white, suffused dark rose, darker ron on margins; lip white, overlaid rose, red on margins and tip, callus yellow; column white;  substance firm; texture crystalline.

location: National Cheng Kung University Fall Orchid Show, Taiwan
description: Twenty-eight flowers on two 52-cm pendulous inflorescences; sepals and petals ivory- white, petals reflexed; lip acuminate, full, flat, ivory-white, 15.4cm spur sparkling ivory-white, bronze tint; column ivory-white; substance firm; texture matte.

Thirteen flowers and two buds on five 6.6-cm inflorescences; on a leafless plant without pseudobulbs grown on a 15x12-cm cork mount; flowers yellow-green; lip nectary white, green distal end, 2.3cm;  substance average; texture matte; submitted to SITF for verification of identity.
Four well-displayed flowers on one inflorescence; sepals cream, striped cordovan; petals cream tinted green, striped cordovan; pouch pale green overlaid rose brown; substance firm; texture waxy.

Thirty-two flowers and 29 buds on three up to 41-cm inflorescences with short branches; sepals and petals white flushed pale pink, finely spotted darker pink apical third, more so on petals; lip pale pink, bold yellow keels, random blotches dark pink centrally; column and anther cap light pink; substance light; texture matte.

One well-held velvety flower and one bud on one 33-cm upright unstaked inflorescence;  sepals red-orange; petals lanceolate, red-orange, darker distal tips; pouch yellow, exterior heavily overlaid red-orange, darker venation, undulate front margin; staminode yellow blushed red-orange; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Six flowers and two buds on eight upright inflorescences up to 17 cm; dorsal sepal white overlaid fuchsia darkening on cauda; lateral sepals fuchsia, darker inferior surface, caudae dark fuchsia; petals white; lip dark fuchsia; column white; substance heavy; texture velvety; petals and lip dimentions estimated, not measured.

crossvalue: (Phalaenopsis Tai Lin Red Angel x Phalaenopsis Dou-dii Golden Princess)
description: Fifteen flowers on two inflorescences to 61cm long; dorsal sepal lemon yellow with fuchsia pink blush and spotting basally, lateral sepals lemon yellow with darker fuchsia spotting centrally; petals lemon yellow with fuchsia pink blush and heavier barring centrally; lip fuchsia pink, calli egg yolk yellow with fuchsia pink spots; column white; substance firm; texture matte.

Two flowers slightly crowded on one 14.2-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals lanceolate, undulate throughout, olive green, spotted mahogany intensifying distally; lip spatulate, flat, white, midlobe yellow basally, veined indigo; column enclosed, white edged indigo, anther cap white; substance firm; texture waxy.

Seventy-two symmetrically arranged flowers on 72 inflorescences on a 23-cm x 17-cm plant growing on a 4-cm x 17-cm cork slab; sepals shiny rose, caudae light yellow-green; petals white; lip white, yellow at tip; substance firm; texture glossy.

Two hundred seventy-six flowers and 516 buds on 12 inflorescences up to 32cm in length;  sepals and petals chartreuse boldly marked dark cordovan coalescent blotches; lip yellow-green sidelobes overlaid brown stripes fusing to solid distally, midlobe yellow overlaid brown basally, bright yellow distally; column light green weakly overlaid brown spots, anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Phragmipedium Haley Decker x Phragmipedium Eric Young)
description: One flower and one bud on one upright inflorescence; dorsal sepal slightly hooked, cream overlaid dark pink; synsepal light yellow, overlaid dark pink, darker on edges; petals slightly sweeping forward, cream overlaid dark pink, darker distally; pouch exterior maroon, interior light yellow spotted maroon; staminode light yellow, overlaid pink; substance firm; texture crystalline.

location: Santa Clara Valley Orchid Society Show
description: Three flowers on three inflorescences; sepals cream brushed with pink, green at tips; petals cream brushed with dark-pink; lip intense burgundy; substance firm; texture matte.

Thirty-one flat flowers on three up to  84-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals light chartreuse marked heavy brown; lip ruffled, mildly fimbriate, white, tiny brown spots side lobe edges, callus fimbriate, yellow overlaid brown; column white, wings edged brown, anther cap white, brown markings; substance firm; texture matte; provisional, sent to SITF.

Two well presented flowers on two inflorescences; sepals white overlaid with pale pink on distal 3/4 fading to pale green at apex; petals white overlaid with darker pink, slightly striated; lip white, keel cream; substance firm; texture matte.
Twenty-five flowers and 25 buds on one branched inflorescence; sepals and petals pale green, pink tips, lateral sepals slightly darker green; lip fuchsia; substance firm; texture matte.

Eight non-resupinate female flowers on one erect inflorescence; sepals green overlaid mahogany basally; petals green overlaid dense spotted mahogany, much less dense centrally; lip green spotted interior mahogany; column chartruse; substance very firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Vibrant Bliss x Cymbidium Amber Wall)
description: Twenty-one round, flat flowers and one bud evenly arranged on one 98.5-cm  arching inflorescence, eight buds on a 56-cm arching inflorescence; sepals clear yellow, dorsal sepal faint red stripe centrally; petals clear yellow; lip slightly ruffled, white, yellow distally, dark red blotches near lower margins and centrally, sidelobes overlaid yellow; column yellow, faintly blushed red, anther cap yellow;  substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium First Dance x Cymbidium Shanghai Spots)
description: Eighteen flowers on one 67-cm arched inflorescence, measured to the terminal flower; sepals and petals cream flushed dark dusty rose, spotted dark purple-maroon overall, spots coalesced at midrib of petals; lip intense dark maroon, edged cream, keels yellow spotted dark maroon; column cream, spotted dark maroon, anther cap maroon; substance firm; texture satin, lip velvet.

Four flowers on two up to  26-cm inflorescences, two immature inflorescences, one capsule on one inflorescence; sepals transluscent ivory; petals reflexed translucent ivory; hypochile bright white, fine burgundy spots; column light green, wings ivory, anther cap light yellow; substance firm; texture matte, hypochile and column waxy; noted floral fragrance.

Three thousand five hundred twenty-six flowers on eighty-two inflorescences; a leafless epiphyte with a symmetrical crown of roots, 34 cm horizontal by 63 cm vertical, growing in a 15 cm wood basket; flower bell-shaped; sepals and petals white; lip white with dark-russet basal spots; anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Twenty-five flowers and five buds on five inflorescences, additionally four immature inflorescences; sepals and petals white, orange-yellow markings proximally; lip white, yellow markings; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Two flowers and one bud on three inflorescences; dorsal sepal golden yellow overlaid with dark orange, darker in three stripes; lateral sepals dark orange with darker venation; petals white; lip purple; substance firm; texture waxy.

location: National Cheng Kung University Fall Orchid Show, Taiwan
crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Hsinying Citron x Paphiopedilum Alma Gevaert)
description: One large, full, flat flower on one tall 31-cm erect inflorescence; sepals white, bold green striping; petals white, intense concentrated green striping and a few spots; pouch lime green; staminode lime green, intense emerald markings centrally; substance firm; texture matte.

Fifteen flowers on one 12.2-cm upright cut inflorescence;  flowers white; sepals and petals heavily suffused dark purple margins and distally; lip spatulate, side lobes overlaid dark purple, midlobe saturated dark purple, keel white; substance firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Hawaiian Illusion x Paphiopedilum Petula's Peacock)
description: One flower and one bud on one 17-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal cream heavily overlaid mahogany, prominately veined darker mahogany, chartreuse proximally; synsepal cream overlaid mahogany proximal third and edges, veined darker mahogany, chartreuse proximally; petals burgundy, chartreuse proximally, hirsute edges; pouch burgundy; staminode chartreuse, burgundy distal edge; substance firm; texture glossy.

Approximately 300 flowers and approximately 200 buds on 15 arching inflorescences held forward on a compact mounted plant; flowers orange; substance firm; texture matte; commended for pleasing presentation of flowers and floriferousness.

crossvalue: (Epidendrum Sun Valley x Epidendrum Pacific Vista)
description: One hundred twenty-seven umbellate evenly spaced full flowers and 120 buds on five up to 25.3-cm upright inflorescences; sepals and petals orange suffused red; lip tri-lobed, lanciniate, yellow-orange overlaid yellow basally, slighly stippled red; column red, yellow distally; substance medium; texture crystalline, lip matte.

Two exceptionally flat flowers on one pendulous inflorescence; sepals and petals cream, broadly and uniformly spotted mahogany, solid mahogany basally; lip cream, speckled mohagany, solid mahogany basally; substance heavy; texture waxy.

Thirty-eight full flowers and 25 buds on six upright inflorescences up to 21.5cm; sepals and petals white,  marked medium burgundy basally, light burgundy edges; lip white, midlobe marked dark yellow, sidelobes marked burgundy; anther cap white; substance hard; texture slightly crystalline.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Dorothy Rowe x Cymbidium Red Beauty)
description: Eighteen slightly starry flowers on one 107-cm staked, upright inflorescence, six buds on a juvenile inflorescence; sepals and petals cream overlaid rose, darker rose veining, narrow white edges; lip cream, midlobe boldly barred and marked bugundy, edged white, keels yellow marked burgundy, side lobes barred and marked burgundy; column superior surface rose shading to dark rose distally, inferior surface barred burgundy, anther cap white; substance medium; texture matte.

One flower on one 33.5-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal medium green, marked with three irregular vertical chestnut stripes; synsepal lighter green, marked with two vertical chestnut stripes; petals green, heavily striped chestnut centrally, strongly overlaid mauve apically; pouch light green overlaid light brown; substance firm; texture waxy.

Approximately one hundred seven flowers and approximately 49 buds on approximately 34 inflorescences; 14.1-cm x 11.3-cm plant grown on a 6-cm x 7-cm cork mount; sepals and petals white; lip white, green markings, green spur;  substance firm; texture matte; foliage exceptionally clean.

One flower on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal green with burgundy distinct spots, large white margin; synsepal green with random burgundy spots; petals base color green, upper half tan-brown, lower half lighter tan-brown with faint venation, red-brown proximally; pouch base color green overlaid red-brown, midline stripe, red-brown interior with burgundy stripe; staminode butter-yellow overlaid faint red; substance medium; texture glossy.
Eight flowers crowded on two 18-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals flat, chartreuse; lip tubular, cream, overlaid chartreuse centrally, faint pink spots in throat;  substance firm; texture matte.

Approximately 1,400 flowers on nine inflorescences, gracefully arranged cylindrically on three pseudobulbs, borne on a mounted plant, front pseudobulb having six inflorescences, middle pseudobulb two inflorescences, back pseudobulb one inflorescence, foliage pristine; sepals and petals ivory suffused dark pink, white apically; lip maroon, white on distal half;  column maroon, anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture crystalline; awarded for pristine foliage and graceful compact inflorescences.
One flower on one inflorescence; on an 8-cm long plant mounted on a 6-cm x 10-cm plaque; sepals and fused petals cream flushed faint pink; lip white;	column yellow; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Lambert Day 'Tangerine Glaze' x Cymbidium Karen Hawaiian 'Hatfields')
description: Sixteen flowers on one 83.5-cm arched inflorescence; sepals and petals yellow overlaid light maroon, veined deep maroon midline, yellow picotee; lip bright yellow spotted deep burgundy basally, midlobe blotched and diffused deep burgundy apically, burgundy midline, yellow picotee, side lobes spotted deep burgundy; column yellow suffused burgundy, striped burgundy ventrally, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Fourteen flowers on one inflorescence, and four immature inflorescences; sepals and petals green; lip white with yellow striations and spots, yellow hairs on keels; column yellow, tipped green toward anther cap; substance average; texture matte. Noted for album color variety.

crossvalue: (Cattleya Circle of Life x Rhyncholaeliocattleya Hisako Akatsuka)
description: Four round, flat, full flowers on two 11.2-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals deep magenta; lip dark magenta distally, throat golden yellow; column white overlaid pale lavendar, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Eleven flowers and four buds on one inflorescence; sepals and petals base color dark purple with variable blotches outlined in lavender; lip pale lavender with dark blotches of maroon and yellow crest; substance heavy; texture waxy.

Eleven full flowers and one bud on two branched up to 52-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals white; lip white, magenta basally; substance medium; texture matte; some segments with variable magenta markings.

Fifty-nine flowers and 131 buds on 190 inflorescences on a 35-cm by 25-cm plant mounted on a cork branch; dorsal sepal cream overlaid burgundy; lateral sepals cream lightly speckled burgundy; petals and lip insignificant; caudae burgundy; substance papery; texture matte; plant well-grown with pristine foliage.

Five striking flowers on two inflorescences; sepals and petals red-bronze veined darker bronze, cream basally; lip white veined dark purple in throat coalescing to dark red-purple centrally, lighter purple distally; substance firm; texture matte.

Nine flowers and two buds on one 96-cm inflorescence;   sepals white overlaid light green, burgundy spots and stripes, burgundy blush marginally; petals white, overlaid light green, burgundy stripes, blushed burgundy marginally; lip margin ruffled, white, blotched burgundy along edges, central burgundy stripe; column white, blushed burgundy, burgundy stripes ventrally, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Eleven xanthic flowers and 12 buds on two arching inflorescences;  sepals and petals pale yellow, asymmetric intense yellow blotches around edges and centrally; lip yellow, butterscotch blotch centrally, intense yellow blotches near edges, callus orange-yellow; column and anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture waxy.

Twenty-four flowers and 30 buds on six 46-cm  inflorescences; sepals and petals uniformly rich orange-red; lip ruffled apically, cream heavily overlaid magenta on margin, finely veined magenta centrally, diffused lighter rust-red apically; substance medium; texture satin.

crossvalue: (Cattleya Brabantiae x Cattleya Pao de Acucar)
description: Three flowers on one 15-cm inflorescence; flowers green overlaid dusty rose-bronze; sepals spotted dark purple, more concentrated on lateral sepals; petals heavily spotted dark purple; reverse of flower heavly spotted dark purple; lip white, side lobes yellow centrally blushed pink, ruffled midlobe flushed bright magenta; substance very firm; texture waxy, lip diamond dust.

Two well-presented flowers on one 25-cm staked inflorescence; sepals ovoid acute, white veined burgundy; petals lanceolate, angled downward, margin undulate, white veined burgundy, darker at tips; pouch white heavily overlaid light burgundy, darker veins; staminode white overlaid burgundy margin to apex, green centrally;  substance firm; texture matte.

Four flowers on one upright inflorescence; dorsal sepal and synsepal light green, striped dark mahogany; petals light green, striped and dotted mahogany, slightly twisted distally; pouch green, overlaid mahogany; staminode light green, hirsut, overlaid dark mahogany; substance firm; texture matte.

Approximately two hundred eighty flowers on 14 arching inflorescences; plant 99cm wide, 33cm tall, grown in a 24-cm pot; sepals and petals white; lip white overlaid pink markings distally, yellow keels; anther cap white; substance moderately firm; texture matte.

Eighteen flowers and three buds on 21 33-cm inflorescences; on a well-grown, clean plant of 34cm x 27cm in a 15-cm clay pot; dorsal sepal burnt orange heavily overlaid dark red, cauda oxblood; lateral sepals blood red obscurely striated black-red, caudae oxblood; petals white; lip saturated oxblood; substance heavy; texture matte. Reference additional award #20185576.

Thirty flowers and 18 buds on three mature inflorescences; dorsal sepal hooded, green, edged orange; lateral sepals cream, edged orange; petals intense orange, tucked under dorsal sepal; lip dark orange, midlobe bifurcate, 4.1-cm nectary light orange basally, dark orange distally; substance medium; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Wossner Ministar x Paphiopedilum In-Charm Lovely)
description: One flower on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal light yellow-green, spotted maroon centrally, white edge; synsepal light yellow-green; petals light yellow-green overlaid mauve, fine mauve spotting apically; pouch light yellow-green overlaid mauve; staminode light yellow-green overlaid mauve, green spot centrally;  substance average; texture glossy.

Eighteen flowers and 14 buds on six evenly arranged up to 81-cm inflorescences; 345-cm circumference plant in a 25-cm plastic azalea pot; dorsal sepal chartreuse, veins heavily marked dark mahogany; synsepal light chartreuse, narrow mahogany veins; petals chartreuse, burgundy spots and veins coalescing to dark burgundy distal half; pouch chartreuse overlaid mahogany, darker mahogany venation; staminode cream, blushed mahogany, hirsuite upper margins; substance firm; texture matte; previous FCC award 20202258.

location: National Cheng Kung University Fall Orchid Show, Taiwan
description: Four hundred forty-eight flowers and 55 buds on 28 cascading inflorescences up to 78 cm; plant exceptionally well flowered, 128 cm tall, 140 cm wide, grown in pumice pellets and New Zealand sphagnum moss mix in 40-cm round plastic pot; sepals white, faintly striated fuchsia; petals white, intensely flashed purple; lip white, overlaid purple, more prominent basally, turning to veins proximally; anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cattleytonia Peggy San x Cattleya Angel Eyes)
description: Three flowers on one 10-cm inflorescence; sepals pale rose; petals white overlaid saturated magenta, white proximally, one dark red spot on each; lip white overlaid saturated magenta distally, yellow throat; column and column wings white; substance firm; texture velvet.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Da Vinci x Cymbidium Dorothy Rowe)
description: Twenty-five flowers on two up to 73-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals pink, darker pink venation; lip cream, picotee, dark burgundy chevron apically, yellow callus, side lobes speckled burgundy marginally; column light burgundy, fading basally, anther cap cream; substance firm; texture matte.

Fourteen flowers on two up to 35-cm inflorescences;  sepals and petals round, flat, slight fenestrations between dorsal sepal and petals, white overlaid dark purple spots coalescing at distal edges; lip white, side lobes overlaid light purple, midlobe overlaid dark purple, throat dark purple stripes; column white blushed pink centrally, anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Six stellate, realtively flat flowers with upright dorsals on two unsupported up-to 23-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals lanceolate, pale suffuse indigo; lip margin ruffled, indigo distally, throat white; column arched, white, anther cap white; substance average; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Odette's Moment x Paphiopedilum President Fred)
description: One flower on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal wine red, darker veining, white edges; synsepal white,overlaid light green, dark wine red veins; petals wine red, darker midrib, very dark hirsuite edges; pouch uniform wine red; staminode beige, flushed red; substance average; texture matte.

One hundred thirteen flowers and 79 buds on seven 28-cm to 42-cm inflorescences, 21 buds on one 28-cm immature inflorescence; sepals and petals cream-white; lip cream-white, keel yellow; anther cap white; substance firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Pink Champagne x Cymbidum Red Beauty)
description: Eighty-five flowers and nine buds on eight erect inflorescences well presented above foliage; five pseudobulbs, 160-cm diameter, 106-cm tall plant grown in a 20-cm round plastic pot; sepals and petals cream, suffused dark rose, linear spots, burgundy central lines; lip white, bugundy spots, midlobe edged burgundy apically; substance firm; texture matte.

Five flowers on three simultaneous inflorescences at one node, four flowers on three simultaneous infloresceences at a second node, one flower on one infloresence; sepals and petals dark violet-purple, white proximally, white tips; broad lip darker violet purple, white proximally, dark purple veins in throat; column and anther cap white; substance average; texture shiny.

Three hundred eighty-eight flowers on 15 upright 12-cm inflorescences; plant 41cm wide x 39.5cm tall, grown in 24-cm pot, no media; sepals and petals light pink; lip dark pink; column pink, anther cap intense pink; substance average; texture matte; also awarded #20225254 CCM 85 points.

Sixteen stellate flowers and four buds on seven upright inflorescences to 13cm; sepals and petals light green, very light brown venation; lip cream, throat golden yellow, magenta venation, side lobes rose-pink transverse; column cream, speckled magenta, anther cap light yellow, speckled magenta; substance medium; texture satin.

Three flat flowers on one 24-cm inflorescence;  sepals and petals chartreuse, lightly veined and suffused red, darker basally; lip cream overlaid light yellow, keels yellow tipped red distally, midlobe spotted and flushed dark red; column chartreuse, dark red ventral surface, anther cap cream; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Six flat stellate flowers and four buds on three up to 18-cm inflorescences;  sepals and petals orange yellow, blushed red, red veins; lip yellow heavily overlaid magenta except throat, side lobes enclose column, throat veined magenta, keels yellow tinged red; substance firm; texture diamond dust.
Three flowers on one inflorescence; sepals and petals white; lip white overlaid lavender-purple, yellow centrally, midlobe striated dark maroon, margins wavy;  substance firm; texture crystalline.

Approximately two hundred eight flowers and forty-two buds on thirteen inflorescences borne on a bark-mounted plant with 16 canes, the longest of which 30 cm in length and 0.9 cm in width; leaves lanceolate, 6.4 cm in length, 1.4 cm in width; petals and sepals nearly translucent, pale magenta; lip purple, providing an excellent focal point for the flower; substance thin; texture glossy; a small, novel, beautiful species of section Calyptrochilus.

One imposing flower and one bud on two 33-cm inflorescences; sepals bright yellow veined darker yellow, caudae transition to orange at tips; petals pale yellow; lip pale yellow, medium yellow at tip; substance very hard; texture waxy, diamond dust.

crossvalue: (Phalaenopsis Penang Girl x Phalaenopsis Black Eagle)
description: Two flowers on two inflorescences; dorsal sepal golden-yellow, overlaid magenta spots; lateral sepals golden-yellow, heavily overlaid magenta inferiorly, thinning to spots superiorly; petals golden-yellow, magenta barred proximally; lip and column white, overlaid bright fuchsia; substance heavy; texture waxy.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Fred's Aura x Paphiopedilum Oriental Jewel)
description: One balanced flower on one 22-cm inflorescence; sepals white, green and rose venation, slight rose blush;  petals heavily spotted burgundy, bright green centrally, green and rose venation, fading along petal length, faint rose blush distally; pouch green heavily overlaid burgundy;  substance firm; texture matte.

Ten flowers and two buds on one inflorescence, two buds on one immature inflorescence; dorsal sepal hooded, light pink-olive; lateral sepals rose-tan; lip light pink, darker basally, nectary tan-orange, 4.7cm; substance firm; texture matte.

One hundred sixty-two flowers on fifty-eight inflorescences grown in a 50 cm diameter pot; sepals old gold striped rose; petals dark pink; lip dark magenta margins with yellow throat striped with magenta; substance firm; texture matte.

Four flowers and two buds on two upright inflorescences up to 13cm long; sepals lanceolate, white marked green at tip; petals white overlaid purple edge and distal half; lip strongly frilled central margin, side lobes touching over column, white, strongly marked purple margins; column white mostly overlaid purple, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

One flower on one 44 cm inflorescence; sepals medium green veined cordovan; petals light green tesselated cordovan; pouch pale green finely speckled cordovan on interior; staminode white, dark burgandy at tip; substance firm; texture matte.

One flower on one 36-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal flat, white, strongly marked green veins ; synsepal light green, darker green veins; petals spatulate, undulate, cream overlaid chartreuse basally, light rose distally, mahogany spots basal two-thirds; pouch light green, overlaid light rose, darker rose veins; staminode cream, green markings; substance firm; texture glossy.

Nine flowers on two 25-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals white blushed lavender, petals darker at lateral margins; lip white, blushed lavender, midlobe magenta, side lobes magenta at the distal margin; column blushed lavender; pollen cap pale yellow; substance firm; texture crystalline

Six well spaced flowers on one inflorescence; sepals yellow with heavily coalesced cordovan spots; petals light yellow with coalesced cordovan spots; side-lobes orange, spaded midlobe white with coalesced cordovan spots, margins fringed cordovan; column white;  substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Hawaiian Illusion x Paphiopedilum Petula's Peacock)
description: One flower on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal chartreuse, maroon veins, off-white margin distally; synsepal green, maroon veins; petals chartreuse overlaid dark maroon, dark purple spots centrally, hirsuite edges; pouch dark maroon; staminode chartreuse overlaid maroon;  substance average; texture glossy.

crossvalue: (Lycaste Chita Melody x Lycaste Alan Salzman)
description: One full flat flower on one inflorescence; sepals cream, heavily overlaid pink centrally to green distal tips, creating charming halo effect at base of segments; petals white, suffused rose-pink distally to recurved margins; lip white, yellow blush in throat, side lobes blushed pink; substance firm; texture matte.

Five flowers on five inflorescences; flower base color chartreuse; dorsal sepal striped dark burgundy centrally, hirsute margins; lateral sepals heavily overlaid intense burgundy, fading to green distally, tips twisted; petals thin burgundy stripes, hirsute marginally; lip hinged, intense burgundy; substance firm; texture pebbled.

One flat flower on one 9.5-cm inflorescence; sepals white veined green; petals slightly undulate, white heavily veined green, burgundy line midrib fading to spots proximally, overlaid rose distally, margins hirsuite, raised bugundy spots proximal half; pouch yellow-green overlaid dark rose, heavily veined dark green; staminode green; substance medium; texture waxy.

Twenty-five flowers and six buds on four infloresences, plus two immature infloresences; sepals rose-tan; petals intense orange-rose; lip intense orange-rose basally, light pink elsewhere, faint orange-rose picotee, nectary rose-tan, 5.0cm long; substance firm; texture matte. Plant entered as Habenaria erichmichelii.

One well-presented flower on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal light green overlaid with dark green and maroon mosaic pattern; synsepal light green fading to rose to cream distally, overlaid with reticulation dark green fading to maroon distally; petals tiny and pale yellow with maroon apex; lip hinged, light green overlaid with maroon spots; anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Twelve flowers on two up to 12-cm inflorescences; flowers white; sepal tips green; petals ruffled, midrib blushed pale green; lip ruffled, pale green blush centrally; substance firm; texture diamond dust.

One hundred sixty flowers and 18 buds on 22 upright 38-cm inflorescences; 50 x 60-cm plant growing in a 23-cm plastic pot; sepals white blushed pale pink; petals white; lip white, throat dark maroon striations, yellow central callus,  pink distally; substance firm; texture satin.  Reference award #20174105.

Approximately 4600 flowers on 92 inflorescences; on an 80-cm x 80-cm plant grown in a 24-cm plastic pot; flowers concolor orange; dorsal sepal formed a lid over succate connate lateral sepals; column yellow; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum President Fred x Paphiopedilum Magically Wood)
description: One symmetrical flower on one 23.2-cm inflorescence; arising from a 3-growth 21.5-cm plant; sepals white overlaid green centrally, rose suffused marginally, venation green; petals white, basally green, distally rose, veining cordovan, random deep mahogany raised spots, superior margins hirsute; pouch maroon, veining darker maroon; staminode light green, dark green centrally; substance firm; texture glossy.

Six flowers on six inflorescences; sepals and petals deep fuchsia, white distally; lip deep fuchsia, dark orange edge, striated black band on margin, interior orange; substance heavy; texture crystalline.
Four flowers and three buds on seven inflorescences; sepals and petals yellow; lip yellow, throat orange; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Fred's Moon 'Lehua's Glow' x Paphiopedilum Fred's Magic 'Lightly Peppered')
description: One flower and one bud on one cut inflorescence; dorsal sepal and synsepal cream, striped bright green; petals cream, striped and flushed green basally, flushed light maroon distally, small dark maroon spots overall; pouch green, flushed and veined dark maroon; staminode cream, veined green centrally, flushed maroon edge; substance moderate; texture matte; slight damage in transit.

One flower on one upright inflorescence; dorsal sepal light yellow, lightly overlaid red, deep red veins and cauda; lateral sepals red, deep red veins and caudae; petals deep red; lip deep red; substance heavy; texture velvety.

One full flower and one bud on two up to 32-cm inflorescences; sepals bright magenta, dark magenta venation, dorsal cauda magenta, red-brown tips all caudae; minute petals white; minute lip white tipped yellow; substance firm; texture velvet.

Two well-balance fragrant flowers on two up-to 15-cm inflorescences; sepals lanceolate, pale green blushed pink distally, lightly veined pink; petals porrect, cream veined pink, heavily marked maroon medially; lip recurved, white spotted maroon; substance firm; texture matte.

One flower and one bud on one 13.5-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal cream overlaid green centrally, bronze veins lower third, 0.6-cm cream margin; synsepal green; petals light green barred magenta, margins undulate, hirsute; pouch cream overlaid mauve increasing intensity from top to bottom; substance firm; texture matte.

Six slightly cupped flowers and 17 buds on three upright to arching inflorescences measuring up to 12.5cm long; sepals and petals vibrant electric purple; lip half-tubular, white, dark purple overlay; column white; substance firm; texture slightly waxy.

Sixty-two flowers and 19 buds on 81 inflorescences, typical infloresence 17cm; well-grown 63-cm diameter plant in a wooden basket; dorsal sepal burgundy, white tesselation proximally; lateral sepals burgundy, dusted white, fading to white distally; petals burgundy, whisker-like, projecting forward; lip green;  substance soft; texture matte;  also recieved award# 20194813.

Three stellate flowers on one 10-cm upright inflorescence; sepals and pteals lanceolate, bright lime green; lip tubular bell, pale yellow-green, throat bright lime green spotted burgundy; column lime green, white apically, anther cap yellow overlaid green; substance firm; texture waxy.

One flower on one 2.7-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal and petals slightly reflexed, sepals and petals bold purple; lip closed and crossed over column, dark magenta, vibrant magenta apically; substance medium; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Len Southward x Cymbidium Rose Armstrong)
description: Twenty-two flowers on one arched inflorescence; sepals and petals light green; lip pale green-yellow, sparsely speckled light cordovan at apex; substance firm; texture matte.
Three hundred fifty-four flowers and 38 buds on six inflorescences; sepals and petals chartreuse; lip proximal third oxblood, distal two-thirds chartreuse; substance firm; texture matte.

One hundred fifty-nine flowers and 160 buds on 40 inflorescences; grown in a 20-cm clay pot; sepals and petals rich vibrant purple, lighter basally; lip white heavily overlaid rich purple, narrow margin white, white centrally; substance heavy; texture matte.

Thirty-nine flowers and two buds on five arching to pendulous inflorescences; dorsal sepal hooded, yellow heavily ovelaid and blotched dark brown-burgundy; lateral sepals lanceolate, yellow, very heavily ovelaid and blotched dark brown-burgundy; petals lanceolate, reflexed, yellow very heavily ovelaid and blotched dark brown-burgundy coalescing centrally; lip pale yellow, blotched dark burgundy; column light yellow spotted burgundy, overlaid burgundy distally, anther cap cream;  substance firm; texture matte.

An island of display at the show entrance, plants grown by many members of the San Francisco Orchid Society, comprised of a wide variety of orchid genera; large, well-grown specimen size cymbidiums and dendrobiums were the focal point of the display, surrounded by paphiopedilums, phragmipediums, cattleyas, rossioglossums, and may other genera, against a backdrop of a pine tree, with white phalaenopsis placed throughout the display to draw the eye from point to point; a unicorn and a tall mushroom with a giant dragon fly showcased the theme of the show: Orchids of the Enchanted Forest.

Ten flowers on two 43-cm canes; sepals and petals lavender, white proixmal end, darker lavender veins, white spot distally; lip flat, white proximally, prominent purple veins, white spot distally; column white; substance firm; texture crystalline.

One full flower on one arching inflorescence; sepals vibrant orange, hirsute magenta, concentrated proximally on dorsal sepal, coalesced to vertical stripes; petals white; lip black; substance heavy; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Rhyncattleanthe Shinfong Little Love x Cattleya coccinea)
description: Three flowers well-presented on one upright 5.0-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals bright yellow heavily overlaid scarlet, petals transition to bright yellow proximally; lip bright yellow, distal margin bright scarlet; substance very firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Aerangis leuteoalba v. rhodosticta x Aerangis hyaloides)
description: Approxiamately four hundred twenty-five flowers and 25 buds on 25 left-sweeping up-to 26-cm inflorescences; incredibly well-grown, immaculate, very compact plant, 22 cm wide, 15 cm tall, 16-cm hardwood branch mount; flowers white; sepals and petals lanceolate; lip spatulate, spur 1.8 cm; column and anther cap bright yellow; substance medium; texture diamond dust.

location: Peninsula Orchid Society and Gold Coast Cymbidium Society Show
description: One hundred flowers on 18 up to 15-cm inflorescences and seven buds on three immature inflorescences; 91-cm x 50-cm plant grown in 34-cm plastic pot; sepals and petals lanceolate, white overlaid light mauve; lip tubular, white overlaid light mauve, dark purple distally; column white, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte; also awarded #20245280 CCE.

Eleven slightly crowded flowers on one  9-cm inflorescence;  sepals recurve at tips, light yellow; petals forward, recurve at tips, light yellow; lip ruffled, light yellow, bright yellow throat overlaid maroon veins, white tip; substance medium; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum President Fred x Paphiopedilum Magically Wood)
description: One stately flat full flower on one sturdy 25.5-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal white, veined green-brown, overlaid green basal half, transitioning to light burgundy on marginal two-thirds; synsepal green, burgundy stripes; petals green basal half transitioning to medium burgundy marginally, heavy dark mahogany warts, upper margin hirsute; pouch burgundy, veined darker burgundy; staminode pale green, darker green centrally; substance medium; texture waxy.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Hazel Tyers 'Santa Maria' x Cymbidium Satin Dragon 'Cinnabar')
description: Eleven full round flowers on one 76-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals white, blushed burgundy, burgundy speckles striated longitudinally; lip white, wide dark burgundy band distally, bugundy spots side lobes; column white overlaid burgundy, ventral surface spotted burgundy, anther cap cream; substance firm; texture matte.

Five flowers on one 18-cm pendent inflorescence and one immature inflorescence; sepals flat, rich yellow heavialy spotted cordovan; petals completely reflexed, rich yellow heavily spotted cordovan; hypochile rich yellow marked dark cordovan, 2.9 cm x 4.0 cm, epichile, 3.3 cm x 3.8 cm, and horns translucent ivory spotted cordovan; column green spotted cordovan, wings ivory spotted cordovan; anther cap yellow; substance very firm; texture matte, lip glossy.

Three erect flowers and four buds held high above foliage on seven 42-cm tall inflorescences, and five immature inflorescences; dorsal sepal orange, mid-vein dark red, caudae dark red; lateral sepals intense orange, vertical red lines convergent to solid red caudae; petals pale yellow;lip dark red; substance firm; texture velvety.

Sixty-two flowers and 19 buds on 81 inflorescences, typical infloresence 17cm; well-grown 63-cm diameter plant in a 15-cm slatted wooden basket; dorsal sepal burgundy, white tesselation proximally; lateral sepals burgundy, dusted white, fading to white distally; petals burgundy, whisker-like, projecting forward; lip green;  substance soft; texture matte;  also recieved award# 20194812.

One flower, two mature buds and one juvenile bud on four pendent sequential-blooming 14-cm inflorescences;    sepals pale green heavily spotted purple, dorsal caudae pink-orange front, dark purple back, lateral caudae pale green transitioning to dark purple distally; petals minute, pink-orange; striking large lip light orange veined dark burgundy coalescing proximally; column cream finely spotted black-purple; substance firm; texture matte.

Three hundred forty flowers and four buds on twenty blooming canes on an immaculate, 70 x 55 cm plant growing in a 20 cm pot; sepals and petals white with purple suffusion distally; lip white with intense purple band distally, dark purple spots in throat; substance medium; texture matte.
Eighty-four flowers on ten inflorescences well above 60cm tall plant; sepals and petals cream overlaid amethyst; lip light yellow basally, amethyst distally; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Twelve flowers and 67 buds on three up to 30-cm branched inflorescences; dorsal sepal oblong, white faintly overlaid coerulea; lateral sepals ovate, white faintly overlaid coerulea; petals oblong, slightly porrect, white faintly overlaid coerulea; lip spatulate, white overlaid blue-lavender transitioning to yellow proximally, sidelobes narrow, upright, callus bright yellow spotted purple; column white overlaid coerulea, anther cap white; substance medium; texture crystalline.

Three flowers and four buds on seven inflorescences; convex pubescent sepals cream overlaid light brown proximal, caudae cordovan; petals cream, light brown proximal; lip white; substance firm; texture matte.
Thirty-four flowers on four inflorescences; sepals and petals medium pink, darker veins; lip white, shaded rose and barred raspberry distally; substance firm; texture matte.

Thirty one flat flowers on one branched, arched, 77-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal pink faintly stippled darker pink; lateral sepals pink, stippled dark rose basally; petals pink, flushed darker pink centrally; lip cream, callus yellow, stippled darker rose, side lobes spotted and barred maroon, midlobe dark pink, darker pink speckles; column and anther cap pink; substance medium; texture crystalline.

Twenty flowers and 35 buds on 55 sequentially flowering inflorescences produced from upper leaf surface on a pristine 13.4 x 12.6 x 8.0-cm multi-layered plant ball grown on a 13 x 5-cm tree fern plaque, creating a stunning display of a miniature species; leaves ovate, light green, tessellating dark green, reverse purple; flowers minute complex; sepals light green-brown; petals dark red; column purple-red.

Two flowers on two inflorescences; sepals yellow-green with slight red stripe proximally on midline; petals yellow-green marked with three distinct red lines; lip recurved, white, red markings at tip and side lobes; substance firm; texture matte.

Nine flat flowers well presented on one inflorescence; sepals and petals green overlaid yellow, boldly marked chocolate brown centrally; lip bright yellow, spotted brown; substance firm; texture matte.

One flower and two buds on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal cream overlaid green-bronze with 0.6 cm cream margin; synsepal cream overlaid bright green; petals light green, burgundy markings with hirsute burgundy margin; pouch pale green heavily stippled rose, anther cap green overlaid bronze; substance firm; texture matte.

Thirty-one stellate flowers and 28 buds on 11 up 18-cm inflorescences; flowers white; sepals and petals overlaid light lavender, flared darker distally; lip tubular, throat yellow, edged dark pink; substance firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Stone Lovely x Paphiopedilum Terry Jarvi)
description: One flower on one 33-cm staked inflorescence; dorsal sepal white centrally overlaid chartreuse, veined medium green; synsepal light green overlaid distinctive green veins; petals superior half amber, inferior half light green, light veining throughout, stippled burgundy centrally; full pouch amber, light blush overlaid; staminode light amber; substance firm; texture glossy; slight cupping precluded higher score.

Three hundred eighty-eight flat flowers on 15 upright 12-cm inflorescences; plant 41cm wide x 39.5cm tall, grown in 24-cm pot, no media; sepals and petals light pink; lip dark pink; column pink, anther cap intense pink; substance average; texture matte; also awarded #20225253 AM 83 points.

Twelve well-presented flowers on one 28.5-cm upright inflorescence;  sepals and petals pink, pale venation petal upper margins; lip ruffled, white, magenta venation, bright yellow stripe throat; substance medium; texture matte.

Approximately one thousand four hundred fifty flowers and 62 buds held well above the foliage on 68 mature and four immature up-to 36-cm inflorescences emerging from papery tan bracts; immaculately grown plant 83 cm wide, 59 cm tall, in bark in a 20-cm bulb pan; sepals and petals light chartreuse overlaid burgundy proximally, burgundy stripes, sepals forward, petals porrect; lip light chartreuse heavily overlaid burgundy; substance medium; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Jewel Green x Paphiopedilum Parisienne Venus)
description: One flower on one inflorescence; sepals green, darker green venation, ivory margins; petals green, darker green veins proximally, dark maroon spotting proximal 2/3, rose blush distally; pouch green, darker green veination, overlaid maroon upper margin; staminode dark green blotched maroon;  substance firm; texture waxy.

Eight flowers and 19 buds on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal hooded, light yellow heavily overlaid green, 0.1-cm light yellow margin; lateral sepals light yellow overlaid green, partially reflexed; petals light yellow; trilobed lip yellow, sidelobes deeply fimbriated, spur 4.9cm, green; substance light; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Sarcochilus Kulnura Sanctuary 'Pink Blush' x Sarcochilus Kulnura Gifted 'Pure Spot')
