description: Seventy-seven flat flowers well held at the apex of ten upright inflorescences up to 17cm; sepals and petals white, evenly blotched dark rose; lip saccate, white overlaid yellow, side lobes red; column white; substance firm; texture crystalline.

One flower and one bud on two up to 5.8-cm inflorescences; sepals cream suffused light amethyst, dorsal sepal slightly recurved; petals cream suffused light amethyst, lighter on midridge; lip tubular, cream, saturated purple on side edges, keels saturated purple; substance medium; texture crystalline.

Approximately seven hundred eighty-five flowers and 13 buds on 21 up to 20-cm inflorescences; superbly balanced plant 53 cm x 41 cm on a 7.5-cm x 21-cm cedar plank mount;  flowers yellow; substance firm; texture waxy; several damaged leaves precluded a higher score for this extremely attractive plant.
Approximately 320 flowers and 57 buds on 13 mature infloresences and five immature inflorescences; flowers dark burgundy-red;  substance average; texture matte.

location: Peninsula Orchid Society and Gold Coast Cymbidium Society Show
crossvalue: (Sarcochilus Kulnura Sanctuary 'GeeBee' x Sarcochilus Roberta 'Good Yellow')
description: Thirty-eight flat, nicely presented flowers and 21 buds on eight arching up to 15-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals white, irregularly blotched and coalescing red proximally; lip white, sidelobes overlaid red; column white, blotched red, anther cap white; substance firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Ron Wiley x Cymbidium Flaming Pepper)
description: Fourteen slightly cupped flowers on one 54-cm inflorescence plus five partially open buds on one immature inflorescence; sepals and petals light yellow overlaid oxblood red, darker midline, yellow edges;  lip ivory overlaid burgundy distally, picotee, keels white; column pale yellow spotted darker interior surface, anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Lycaste Pearl Line x Lycaste Chita Dream)
description: Three well spaced flowers and two buds on five inflorescences; sepals and petals medium pink, pink speckles on petals; lip white, heavily spotted burgundy, callus yellow; anther cap cream; substance firm; texture matte.

Two flowers and 15 buds on 17 wiry, erect inflorescences, 17-cm in length, borne on a plant 33cm in diameter, grown in moss in a 17-cm basket; leaves linear, 23-cm in length, 1.6-cm in width; sepals white, flushed and veined dark purple on reverse, pink tomentose, appearing mauve, caudae dark purple; petals white; lip light pink; column yellow; substance firm; texture matte; a recently described species from Columbia.

Two flowers and one bud on one 37-cm arched inflorescence; dorsal sepal undulate, hirsute exterior, cream overlaid green medially, striped cordovan proximally; synsepal undulate, hirsute exterior, green; petals narrow, twisted distally, undulate, ciliate, light green blotched cordovan; pouch cream overlaid rose, speckled darker rose; staminode dark olive green; substance firm; texture matte.

Forty flowers and three buds on 43 inflorescences; plant 41cm wide, 22cm tall in a 13-cm pot; dorsal sepal white, overlaid magenta, cauda magenta basally suffusing to yellow-brown apex; lateral sepals white, magenta basally, stippled fine magenta, caudae intense yellow; minute petals white; lip magenta; anther cap white; substance firm, texture waxy.

Fourteen flowers and four buds on two inflorescences; sepals olive green brushed bronze on reverse; petals light green, lighter at edges; lip white with small burgundy blotch apically; column green with bronze overlay; substance fair; texture matte.

One flower on one 26-cm arching inflorescence; highly hooded dorsal sepal light yellow overlaid medium brown, patterned light yellow spots; lateral sepals yellow-green, muted brown reverse reticulation; petals minute; lip minute, chartreuse spotted burgundy;  substance average; texture matte.

Exhibitor and hybridizer Pierre Pujol; cross recognized for heavily spotted flowers exhibiting the species charm of erythraeum, the Pinata Magic parent accentuating spotting and intensity of color, 17 plants were exhibited, three were awarded for flower quality at this judging, one was previously awarded for flower quality.

Eleven well-presented stellate flowers on a 60.0-cm cut inflorescence; sepals and petals green overlaid cordovan veins, diffused cordovan between veins; lip heavily recurved, white, burgundy spots, hirsuite centrally, side lobes heavily stripped burgundy; column cream, burgundy tip, underside spotted burgundy; substance firm; texture matte.

Five flowers and two buds on one 29.2-cm inflorescence; sepals cream boldly striped deep rose; petals porrect, cream marked rose, deep rose stripe at midline; lip recurved distal edge, cream, blotched deep rose; column pale yellow, anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture matte.
Three flowers on one inflorescence; sepals and petals chartreuse, heavily longitudinally striped mahogany; pouch chartreuse heavily overlaid mahogany; substance firm; texture waxy.

Twelve apparently albinistic flowers and four buds on two inflorescences; sepals and somewhat porrect petals medium yellow; lip yellow, strongly recurved with two darker yellow keels; substance firm; texture matte.

Approximately 145 flowers and 40 buds on 84 inflorescences; well-grown 134-cm plant with clean foliage, in a 40-cm pot; sepals and petals lavendar; lip magenta, dark magenta striations, keel yellow; substance thin; texture matte.
Sixty-two flowers and five buds on fifty-three canes; flowers white; lip fimbriated white with deep yellow-orange keels; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Four flowers on one upright inflorescence 14cm long; sepals lanceolate, white marked green at the tip; petals white overlaid purple margin and distal half, fading proximally; lip strongly frilled central margin, side lobes touching over column, white, strongly marked purple margins; column white mostly overlaid purple, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Twenty-four flowers and 33 buds on three 57-cm upright to arching inflorescences; sepals and petals light yellow overlaid dark burgundy stripes;  lip white, liberally splotched burgundy;   substance average; texture matte.

Sixty-eight delicate flowers on 17 up to 23-cm inflorescences; plant immaculate, 95 cm wide by 63 cm tall, grown in bark in a 30-cm plastic bulb pan; sepals narrow, lanceolate, rolled and recurved distally, white blushed lavender; petals full, porrect, recurved distally, undulate margins, white, heavily blushed lavender, midrib white; lip tubular, flaring, undulate distally, white overlaid yellow, veined magenta basally, magenta distal quarter, picotee; column white, anther cap white; substance medium; texture diamond dust; also received award 20245284.

Forty-five flowers and 18 buds on five upright inflorescences up to 10cm; dorsal sepal curved forward, lavender; lateral sepals slightly cupped, lavender, fading to white at margin; petals cupped, lavender outside, streaked white and lavender inside; lip broad, flat, trilobed, dark lavender, lighter shade at the margin; substance good; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Phalaenopsis Fangmei Dream Wedding x Phalaenopsis Fangmei Yellow Lippe)
description: Twelve full flowers racked well on one arching 78cm inflorescence; sepals and petals smooth pink-lavender, petals lightly veined with slightly darker lavender centrally; lip midlobe and slightly broadened side lobes pink-lavender, throat magenta-spotted on and near white calli; column white, anther cap white blushed with pink; substance average; texture crystalline.

One flower on one inflorescence;  sepals white, veined green; petals cream overlaid green, faint fine darker green veins, heavily spotted mahogany, margins hirsute;   pouch green, upper portion overlaid mahogany, veined mahogany; staminode green;  substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cattleya Lulu x Cattleya Penny Kuroda (Penny Kuroda Gp))
description: Twelve flowers clustered at the top of one very strong 26-cm inflorescence; sepals cream-white suffused rose pink, spotted dark pink, green distal tip; petals cream-white suffused dark pink, distal half spotted darker pink; lip cream-white, side lobes blushed pink, midlobe overlaid dark purple distally; column cream-white, blushed pink margins, anther cap cream-white, pink spot; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Oncidium Joe's Drum x Oncidium Florence Stirling)
description: Sixteen flowers on two maximum 72-cm inflorescences, one branched; sepals and petals white overlaid magenta edges, large irregular mahogany splotches; lip white edged dark pink, bright yellow callus, magenta marks; column white, burgundy markings, column wings bright yellow, magenta marks; substance medium; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Green Glass x Cymbidium Valley Zenith)
description: Fourteen flowers on one 71-cm staked arching inflorescence; sepals and petals medium green, faint pink blush centrally, burgundy basally; lip cream, heavily spotted maroon, coalescing near margin, keel pale yellow spotted burgundy distally; column cream, finely stippled burgundy, anther cap cream; substance firm; texture matte.
Four flowers on one inflorescence; sepals and petals red-bronze; lip white veined dark purple on throat coalescing to dark purple centrally, lighter purple distally; substance firm; texture matte.

Two flat flowers and three buds on three upright 3.5-cm inflorescences;  sepals and petals magenta; lip yellow heavily overlaid magenta except throat, side lobes enclose column, throat veined magenta; anther cap white, center magenta dot; substance soft; texture slightly diamond dust.

crossvalue: (Cattlianthe Sue Fordyce x Cattleya Circle of Life)
description: Two round flowers on one inflorescence; sepals and petals magenta; lip magenta, gold centrally, darker magenta distally; substance firm; texture satin.
Fifty flowers and 51 buds on 29 inflorescences on an 80-cm plant in a 36-cm pot; sepals and petals pale pink; lip fuchsia distally, white with maroon lines centrally; substance fair; texture matte.

Ten flowers and seven buds on two inflorescences; flowers white overlaid faint pink blush on back of dorsal sepal; lip green stripes basally, 3.8-cm nectary tan-green; substance moderate; texture matte.  Plant damaged in-transit.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Memoria Amelia Earhart x Cymbidium Woody Wilson)
description: Thirty-five slightly cupped flowers and one bud on three up to 56-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals apricot yellow, heavily blushed rose, striped darker rose; lip white, midline maroon stripe, maroon spots on edges, side lobes blushed yellow apically, keel yellow, speckled rose; column apricot yellow, speckled rose, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Four flowers and five buds on nine inflorescences; sepals and petals light green blushed pink along margins; lip pale chartreuse, darker centrally, keel edged burgundy; substance hard; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Dendrobium Jaquelyn Concert x Dendrobium Lady Charm)
description: Two hundred fifty shapely and deeply colored flowers 23 graceful inflorescences to 42.6cm long; plant exceptionally well-flowered, 120cm tall, 106cm wide, grown in a 28cm black plastic pot; sepals and petals solid deep purple; lip deep purple, black-purple centrally; column deep purple, anther cap white; substance average; texture satiny.
Eighteen flowers and 20 buds on one branching inflorescence; sepals and petals intense black-purple; lip violet; substance firm; texture waxy.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium James Toya x Cymbidium Flaming Pepper)
description: Nine flowers on one 68-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals brown, striped mahogany; lip cream, burgundy spots and distal band; column burgundy, anther cap cream; substance heavy; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Hazel Tyers 'Santa Maria' x Cymbidium Satin Dragon 'Cinnabar')
description: Group of 13 plants; consistent full shape and good overall color, base color ranging from cream to chatreuse, overlaid pink; one AM (20215304) and two HCCs (20215303, 20215304) were awarded in this group, one AM (20194867) and one HCC (20194861) were previously awarded on the same cross but were not exhibited at this judging.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Len Southward x Cymbidium Doctor Baker)
description: Eighty-seven flowers and six buds on three inflorescences, thirty-seven of the flowers and four of the buds on the longest inflorescence; sepals and petals light green, finely stippled dark rose centrally, coalescing distally; lip white, boldly spotted maroon, suffused rose distally; column cream, stippled light rose, coalesing dark rose distally, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.
One flower on one inflorescence; sepals and petals magenta; lip magenta, darker throat;  substance firm; texture matte.

Forty-seven flowers and eight buds on ten upright staked 62-cm inflorescences facing one direction; immaculately grown 56-cm wide, 96-cm tall plant, 30-cm x 15-cm plastic pot; flowers white, delicately flushed pink-lavender; lip ruffled, white suffused light yellow centrally, red veins in throat, light pink-lavender margins; substance firm; texture diamond dust; higher score precluded by slight mildew on petal reverse on some flowers.

Eight flowers and 26 buds on 34 wiry inflorescences, 16cm in length, borne on a robust floriferous plant, 48-cm in diameter, grown in moss in a 17-cm basket; leaves lanceolate, mostly trimmed apically, 20.0-cm in length, 2.1-cm in width; sepals white, stippled burgundy on front and reverse, darker and smaller proximally, dense light yellow hirsute, caudae dark mahogany; petals white; lip light pink; column white; anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Masdevallia MacInnes' Golden Heart x Masdevallia yungasensis)
description: Two full flowers on two inflorescences average 16.6cm; dorsal sepal cream, caudae light orange distally, striped burgundy, purple hirsute; lateral sepals light orange to orange caudae distally, dark burgundy stripes, purple hirsute; petals cream;  lip dark burgundy; substance firm; texture velvety; remarkable clear color contrast.

Seventeen slightly cupped flowers on one 126-cm staked inflorescence; sepals and petals yellow heavily overlaid coral, magenta veins; lip white, side lobes spotted burgundy, callus yellow, midlobe burgundy distally, light yellow picotee; column cream overlaid burgundy dorsal surface, spotted burgundy ventral surface basally; substance medium; texture matte.
Twelve flowers and eighteen buds on four inflorescences; sepals and petals green, stripped basally maroon; lip recurved, light yellow, maroon spots; column green; substance firm; texture matte.

Sixty-one flowers and 29 buds on 17 inflorescences up to 19cm; vigorous 90-cm wide by 55-cm tall plant in bark, 30-cm plastic pot; sepals and petals magenta; petals undulate swept forward; lip tubular, interior white, heavily veined dark magenta, central stripe bright yellow, margins ruffled; substance medium; texture matte; plant dropped in transit, minor foliage and flower damage, pot cracked.

Twenty-one flowers on three upright inflorescences up to 60cm length; sepals yellow suffused burgundy, most intense on superior surface of lateral sepals; petals yellow, burgundy central vein; lip pale yellow striped dark burgundy distally, spotted dark burgundy centrally; anther cap pale yellow; substance very firm; texture matte.

Thirty-eight flowers evenly distributed on five inflorescences; sepals and petals lanceolate, margins undulate, pink tessellated dark pink; lip tri-lobed dark rose-red veined darker rose-red, side lobes encircling column, mid-lobe long, pointed; substance medium; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Sarcochilus Duno Nicky's Twin x Sarcochilus Heidi)
description: Fourteen flowers and two buds on two inflorescences; sepals and petals dark burgundy, color more intense centally on segments, white marking on reverse; lip yellow overlaid burgundy; substance firm; texture velvety.

One striking flat flower on one inflorescence; dorsal and lateral sepals cream heavily overlaid dark cordovan; caudae deep cordovan fading to tan at apex; petals cream spotted deep cordovan; lip cream; substance heavy; texture matte.

Approximately 5500 flowers on 33 branched inflorescences on a 70-cm x 42-cm plant, grown on an 8-cm x 6-cm treefern mount; dorsal sepal violet; petals and lip white; substance not described; texture matte.

One flat flower on one 23-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal pale yellow, blushed pink basally; synsepal pale yellow; petals slightly wavy, dark pink; pouch pale yellow overlaid pink, speckled interior; substance firm; texture velvety.

Eighteen flowers and 36 buds on three 25.3-cm average erect inflorescences; sepals and petals lanceolate, rich red-purple; lip cream, side-lobes closed over column, suffused rose distally, midlobe magenta, margin ruffled;  substance firm; texture matte, lip velvet.

crossvalue: (Paphiopedilum Autumn Gold x Paphiopedilum White Knight)
description: Three slightly cupped flowers and one bud on three erect inflorescences; sepals white overlaid pale yellow proximally, faintly lined light green; petals white overlaid pale yellow; pouch light yellow;  staminode light yellow; substance firm; texture waxy.

Thirteen flowers and three buds on one infloresence, seven flowers and seven buds on second inflorescence; dorsal sepal green edged orange; lateral sepals cream edged orange; petals intense orange; lip dark orange, 4.8-cm nectary light orange basally, dark orange distally; substance medium; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Phalaenopsis Brother Dendi x Phalaenopsis Brother Sara Gold)
description: Eleven flowers on one branched inflorescence; sepals and petals yellow, lightly suffused fuchsia centrally, small concentric fuchsia bars overall; lip white, side lobes flushed fuchsia with small fuchsia dots, midlobe fuchsia; substance firm; texture matte.

Eighteen flowers and four buds on one branched 38-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals chartreuse boldly blotched burgundy; lip chartreuse, side lobes light cordovan, mid lobe brilliant yellow, keels prominent, brilliant yellow spotted burgundy; column chartreuse spotted burgundy, anther cap bright yellow; substance firm; texture satin.

Three full flowers and 13 buds on 16 inflorescences; sepals pubescence, cream overlaid pale cordovan proximally; caudae cordovan; petals cream; lip cream overlaid pale cordovan; substance firm; texture matte.

One hundred forty-eight flowers flowers on 14 inflorescences arranged attractively around the front half of the pot; plant 110-cm wide grown in a 28-cm pot; sepals and petals dark rose; lip white, heavily spotted burgundy; substance average; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Phalenopsis bellina x Phalaenopsis Dragon Tree Eagle)
description: One flat flower on one inflorescence; sepals and petals white overlaid yellow-green distally, barred intense magenta proximally; lateral sepals proximal inferior half intense magenta; lip intense magenta, side lobes yellow with magenta tips; column and anther cap magenta; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Sarcochilus Kulnura Sanctuary 'GeeBee' x Sarcochilus Roberta 'Good Yellow')
description: Twenty-seven flowers and six buds on three up to 22-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals white, concentric maroon bars basally; lip white, maroon markings interior, yellow-maroon mark apically; column white, anther cap cream; substance firm; texture diamond dust.

Forty-five flowers and four buds on 49 up to 26-cm inflorescences; 75-cm plant in 17-cm plastic pot; dorsal sepal white overlaid yellow, cauda yellow; lateral sepals fused, white, flushed lavendar distally, yellow proximally, caudae yellow; petals  minute, yellow, not measureable; lip minute, yellow, not measurable;  substance average; texture matte.

Thirteen flowers and one bud on two 24-cm staked inflorescences; sepals and petals white veined and suffused dusty rose, more heavily on petals, especially tips; lip white heavily overlaid dusty rose, darker veins, lighter throat;  substance firm; texture matte.

Eight flowers and eight buds on one upright inflorescence; sepals light pink, darker veins distally; petals tri-lobed, mid-lobe pink, side lobes orange; lip porrect, mid-lobe pink,  side lobes orange; substance firm; texture matte.

Four flowers on four 20-37-cm inflorescences; flowers white; sepals overlaid light pink, darker marginally; petals overlaid dark pink-burgundy, lighter centrally; lip burgundy margin, saturated burgundy centrally; substance very firm; texture diamond dust.

One flower on one inflorescence; dorsal sepal wine-purple, lighter apically, dark centrally, darker veins; synsepal light wine-purple, dark veins; petals brown-purple; pouch brown-purple; staminode light wine-purple; substance average; texture waxy.

Eight flowers and fourteen buds on four inflorescences; sepals and petals white; lip white overlaid medially yellow, purple striations base to apex, coalescing to 0.5 cm lavender band distally with white fringed picotee, mid-lobe yellow hirsute base to lavender band, keels dark yellow; substance firm; texture crystalline.

Sixteen flowers and seven buds on 23 inflorescences; well-grown 29-cm x 29-cm plant mounted on a 27-cm x 19-cm cork slab; flowers orange-red; lip gold centrally, veined orange-red; substance firm, texture matte.

Two hundred twenty-eight mainly flat flowers and 67 buds on 27 upright inflorescences; plant 38cm wide, 31cm tall, inflorescence up to 27cm, grown in bark in a 20-cm plastic pot; sepals and petals white, splashed rose, more heavily on sepals, deep oxblood basally; lip yellow, rose markings; substance very firm; texture crystalline.  Also received an AM of 83 points, award #20194870.
Two flowers on two 8.3 cm inflorescences; sepals and petals lavender; lip lavender, overlaid deep purple, throat brushed yellow, purple veins; substance firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Khan Flame x Cymbidium Valley Splash)
description: Twenty-six slightly cupped flowers on two up to 97-cm upright staked inflorescences; sepals ivory overlaid centrally red-pink; petals ivory, midline red-pink, suffused near midline; lip ivory, midlobe picotee, dark red-pink distally, side lobes edged pink, callus yellow; column ivory overlaid and spotted dark pink, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

crossvalue: (Phaleanopsis Yungho Gelb Canary 'Chin Yo' x Phalaenopsis Penang Girl 'Taipei')
description: Seven flowers on two inflorescences; sepals and petals yellow with green suffusion, white centrally, very slight pink suffusion on the medial aspect of lateral sepals; lip white with bright yellow side lobes; substance hard; texture waxy.

location: National Cheng Kung University Fall Orchid Show, Taiwan
description: Thirty-seven flowers and 15 buds on one 31-cm arching inflorescence and one additional inflorescence on keiki off previously flowered inflorescence; sepals and petals white blushed pink; lip white, spotted maroon basally, side lobes two maroon strips centrally, midlobe blushed pink, speckled maroon basal 4/5ths, callus white spotted maroon; column pink, anther cap white; substance medium; texture crystalline; noted for wild-collected native phalaenopsis on Little Orchid Island off southeast coast of Taiwan.

crossvalue: (Alantuckerara Cedar Creek x Galeopetalum Black Knight)
description: Nine flowers on two inflorescences to 40cm long; sepals and petals green heavily suffused maroon to appear dense bronze;  lip white, flushed and veined bright purple, crest light lavender; column green fully overlaid black basally, mottled at tip, anther cap green; substance firm; texture matte.

Fifteen flowers and three buds on one arching inflorescence; dorsal sepal arching, chartreuse, maroon spots coalescing on margins; lateral sepals sweeping forward, maroon spots coalescing on margins;  petals chartreuse, spots and blotches coalescing on margins and distal tips; lip white, blotched red on margin and tip, keel white, ciliate; column cream, spotted red-brown;  substance firm; texture matte.
One flower on one 23-cm inflorescence; sepals cream overlaid rose, veined dark rose, peach basally, caudae orange; petals cream; lip dark rose; substance medium; texture diamond dust.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Love the Moon x Cymbidium Dick Doran)

Twenty-three flowers and one bud evenly displayed on one 154-cm arched inflorescence; sepals dark chartreuse heavily overlaid and veined burgundy, dorsal sepal hooded, lateral sepals swept forward; petals horizontal, margins slightly recurved, dark chartreuse heavily overlaid and veined burgundy, especially midrib, edges dark chartreuse; lip cream, keels spotted burgundy, sidelobes overlaid light yellow, spotted burgundy, midlobe spotted burgundy, medial burgundy line; column light yellow, blushed burgundy dorsally, spotted burgundy ventrally, anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture matte, lip velvety; followed bend on lip for length measurement.

crossvalue: (Oncidium Petit Port x Oncidium Geneva Red)
description: Twelve full,well-balanced flowers and 15 buds on two branched inflorescences; sepals and petals uniform intense red; lip intense red fading centrally, bright yellow crest; column red, white distally, anther cap white; substance hard; texture pearlescent.

location: National Cheng Kung University Fall Orchid Show, Taiwan

Eight stellate flowers and two buds on two branched up to 15.5-cm inflorescences; sepals white randomly overlaid indigo-violet; petals white overlaid indigo-violet; lip white, indigo-blue basally; column white, blotched indigo; substance firm; texture waxy.

Twenty-five full round flowers on two arching approximately 20-cm inflorescences; segments white, semi-transparent, tinged yellow basally; column orange, anther cap light yellow; substance medium; texture crystalline; petaloid.

Eleven flowers and 14 buds on one arching 106-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal hooded, lanceolate, light yellow, densely spotted burgundy; lateral sepals and petals lanceolate, yellow, spotted, blotched and diffused burgundy; lip white overlaid yellow basally, spotted burgundy; column chartreuse, spotted burgundy, anther cap white; substance average; texture matte.

Five hundred twenty-seven ruffled flowers and 108 buds well displayed above the foliage on eight strong multi-branched inflorescences; well-grown plant in 25-cm bulb pan, clean foliage; sepals, pleasantly swept back, and petals bright yellow, barred mahogany; lip bright yellow, central calyx yellow, ridges red, side lobes barred mahogany; column and anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture glossy, lip matte; also received HCC, award #20215327.

Sixteen flowers and 13 buds on one infloresence, seven flowers and eight buds on second inflorescence; dorsal sepal intense salmon pink overlaid green; lateral sepals white basally, intense salmon pink distally; petals salmon pink; lip fringed, intense salmon pink, midlobe slightly darker, 4.8-cm nectary pink overlaid green; substance medium; texture matte.

Two hundred two flowers on 27 arching, branched inflorescences; plant 92cm wide by 112cm tall mounted on a cork plaque 20cm wide by 80cm long; flowers white; lip striped purple, light green basally; substance papery; texture matte.

location: National Cheng Kung University Fall Orchid Show, Taiwan

location: Peninsula Orchid Society and Gold Coast Cymbidium Society Show

Thirteen flowers and eight buds on one inflorescence, three flowers and seven buds on a second inflorescence; dorsal sepal salmon pink overlaid green; lateral sepals white basally, salmon pink disally; petals salmon pink; lip delicate salmon pink, midlobe darker, lateral lobes fringed, spur light salmon pink overlaid light olive green distally; substance firm; texture matte.

location: Peninsula Orchid Society and Gold Coast Cymbidium Society Show

Approximately 61 flowers and 123 buds on 13 up to 2-cm inflorescences; well presented on a clean 38-cm tall x 28-cm wide, or not including roots 22-cm wide, plant mounted on a 30-cm x 9-cm manzanita branch; sepals and petals porrect, white; lip recurved, white; anther cap chartreuse; substance hard; texture crystalline.

location: Peninsula Orchid Society and Gold Coast Cymbidium Society Show

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Red Beauty x Cymbidium Kirbey Lesh)

crossvalue: (Barkeria Michoacan Gem x Barkeria Libby Hodge)

Twenty flowers and four buds on one upright branched inflorescence; sepals and petals chestnut, yellow markings apically; lip chestnut, brown-purple basally, barely spotted yellow; column pale green, anther cap yellow; substance firm; texture shiny.

crossvalue: (Cymbidium Klan Flame x Cymbidium Kabaki Moon)

Sixteen flowers and seven buds on one infloresence; dorsal sepal green, hooded; lateral sepals cream overlaid green, rolled; petals cream, tip orange; lip florescent orange, 4.7-cm nectary orange;  substance moderate; texture matte.

Approximately 2288 flowers in very fine condition and three buds on 12 highly branched inflorescences approximately 151cm long; exceptionally well-grown 137x103-cm plant in bark, 36 flat pseudobulbs 13.5x6cm, leathery leaves 47x9.2cm, 31-cm bulb pan; sepals and petals reflexed, coiled, light chartreuse barred light mahogany; lip white, ruffled side lobes, spotted light brown, claw white spotted light brown, callus yellow spotted light brown; column chartreuse, column wings white spotted light brown, anther cap chartreuse; substance soft; texture matte; all flowers in peak condition influenced the cultural award; see award #20215323 also.

Fourteen flowers and 12 buds on one  79-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal hooded, pristine white; lateral sepals twisted, pristine white; petals reflexed, pristine white; lip spade shaped, pristine white; column white, anther cap white; substance firm; texture slightly waxy.

Two flowers on two inflorescences; dorsal sepal deep red-purple, golden yellow veined red-purple basally; lateral sepals deep red; petals cream, single purple-red stripe central third of midrib; lip intense dark red; column cream edged purple-red along anther cap, striped purple-red along ventral margins; substance firm; texture velvety.
One flower on one inflorescence; sepals orange; petals orange basally, tangerine apically; lip orange, black on distal margine; substance firm; texture crystalline.

crossvalue: Cymbidium serratum x Cymbidium Eastern Venus
description: Three flowers on two upright, up to 21-cm inflorescences; sepals and petals  light green, petals slightly porrect; lip recurved, cream, midlobe randomly spotted burgundy; column light green, ventral surface spotted burgundy, anther cap cream; substance firm; texture matte.

Five relatively flat upright bright pink flowers on one 23-cm unsupported inflorescence; sepals elliptical, tipped green apically; petals widely elliptical, raised midrib basal half; lip ruffled, pink apical edge, overlaid cream blushed pink, side lobes enclose column; column white, anther cap white; substance firm; texture satin.

Thirty flowers and two buds apically clustered on nine up to 82-cm slightly arching inflorescences; flowers white; lip slightly ruffled on margins, stippled magenta , blushed yellow centrally; column white, overlaid light green, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.

Thirteen flowers and two buds on 14 up to 40-cm sturdy inflorescences; presented on a robust 51.5-cm wide, 60.5-cm high plant grown in a 25.4-cm round plastic pot in bark and moss; sepals recurved, cream, veining and margins blushed light fuchsia; petals porrect, recurved apically, cream heavily blushed fuchsia; lip cream, mottled fuchsia, throat and callus bright yellow; column cream tipped pale pink, anther cap cream; substance firm; texture matte; received quality award 20255356.

Thirteen flowers and two buds on 14 up to 40-cm sturdy inflorescences; presented on a robust 51.5-cm wide, 60.5-cm high plant grown in a 25.4-cm round plastic pot in bark and moss; sepals recurved, cream, veining and margins blushed light fuchsia; petals porrect, recurved apically, cream heavily blushed fuchsia; lip cream, mottled fuchsia, throat and callus bright yellow; column cream tipped pale pink, anther cap cream; substance firm; texture matte; received cultural award 20255357.

crossvalue: Paphiopedilum Cocoa Hamana x Paphiopedilum hirsutissimum
description: Two flowers and two buds on two up to 24-cm inflorescences; sepals cream overlaid light chartreuse, spotted and striped mahogany, dorsal sepal spotted coalescing to heavier stripe centrally; petals chartreuse, lightly ruffled on upper margin, superior half overlaid mahogany,  stippled mahogany basally; pouch chartreuse, overlaid light brown; staminode chartreuse, stippled brown sides; substance medium, texture waxy.

crossvalue: Cymbidium So Bold x Cymbidium Cora Paddison
description: Ten striking flowers on one 70-cm inflorescence; sepals and petals golden yellow, veins burgundy, darker burgundy midrib; lip golden yellow overlaid white internally, yellow picotee, burgundy apically, randomly spotted burgundy, keels white spotted burgundy; column gold stippled burgundy, anther cap white; substance hard; texture waxy, lip diamond dust.

Approximately 780 flowers and 72 buds on 56 upright inflorescences up to 25 cm, four are immature; plant 89 cm by x 80 cm, grown in 15-cm plastic pot; flowers white, sepals and petals apically blushed rose, petals swept forward, overlaid light rose distal half; lip stippled medium rose, keel chartreuse; column and anther cap white; substance very firm, texture crystalline.

Two yellow flowers on two upright inflorescences up to 40 cm; dorsal sepal deltoid, veined light green, margin undulate, puberulent; synsepal cordate, veined light green, margin puberulent; petals widely oval, proximal one-third pubescent, margins puberulent; pouch interior linearly spotted cordovan; staminode rhombic, stippled cordovan; substance medium; texture matte.

crossvalue: Dendrobium Peter Shen x Dendrobium Silver Wings
description: Thirty-seven flowers and 26 buds on 12 upright up to 29-cm inflorescences; a beautifully grown plant 67 cm x 70 cm in bark in a 22-cm x 14-cm round plastic pot;  sepal and petals white, sepals lanceolate, lavender spots adaxially, petals ovate, apiculate, undulate, lavender marginal markings adaxially; lip apically pinched, white overlaid lavender, spotted and heavily veined dark lavender; substance medium; texture crystalline.

Multi-level display 122 cm x 400 cm, wide variety of genera, species and hybrids, including dendrobium, cattleya, cymbidium, coelogyne, masdevallia, paphiopedilum, lycaste and maxillaria, colors flowing from pink to yellow to orange, focal point Dendrobium speciosum.

Multi-level display 122 cm x 400 cm, wide variety of genera, species and hybrids, including dendrobium, cattleya, cymbidium, coelogyne, masdevallia, paphiopedilum, lycaste and maxillaria, colors flowing from pink to yellow to orange, focal point Dendrobium speciosum.
